(147, 'Western Sydney University Regional Achievement Award', 'Scholarship for international undergraduate applicants from North Asia and South East Asia completing Australian Year 12, automatically applied towards tuition fees.', 10000.00, 'FIXED', '2026-12-31', 86, 'https://www.westernsydney.edu.au/international/applying/fees-and-costs/scholarships/regional-achievement-award', 'active', '2026-01-19 10:39:48', '2026-04-11 10:05:14', NULL, 'Merit-Based', 'Insufficient detail provided on the source page. The page title and URL indicate this is a Regional Achievement Award for international students, but specific eligibility criteria text was not included in the provided content.', 'No Results Found.\n${html `<div class=\"global-search-panel\">\n<div class=\"global-search__suggestions\">\n${recentSearches}\n${querySuggestions}\n</div>\n<div class=\"search-tab-container\">\n<div class=\"search-tab\">\n${sources[0]}\n<div class=\"search-tab \">\n${sources[1]}\n${sources[2]}\n${sources[3]}\n</div>`}\nREGISTER INTEREST\nInternational Students\nWhere are you from?\nThis will help us find the right content for you.\nAre you an International student?\nLooks like you are viewing this page from Australia\nChange Country\nView Domestic\nInternational Enquiries\n+61 2 9852 5499\nDiscover\nWestern Sydney University is ranked in the top 250 universities globally. Join students from over 170 countries who have turned passions into rewarding careers.\nWhy Western\nSuccess Stories\nRankings and Statistics\nMeet Our Students\nEvents\nOur Campuses\nBankstown City\nCampbelltown\nHawkesbury\nLiverpool City\nMelbourne\nParramatta City\nParramatta South\nPenrith\nIndonesia\nSydney City\nSydney Olympic Park\nWestmead\nAgents\nFind an Agent\nAbout Western\nProspective agent\nBrand, logo & mission\nAdmission procedures\nAgent information\nStudy abroad\nGo Global\nStudying\nUnlock unlimited possibilities through studying with us. Learn more about Western Sydney University, our programs, applications and international study here.\nPrograms for your success\nWestern way of learning\nPre-university pathways\nSetting up your studies\nEarly Offers\nApplying\nNot sure where to begin to apply as an international student? Learn more about applications, finding an agent and other information to apply to study with us.\nCost of tuition\nUS Financial Aid Program\nInternational Sibling Discount\n10% Alumni Postgraduate Discount\nHow to apply\nInternational Application System\nAfter you apply\nAbout your offer\nAccepting your offer\nPaying International Student Fees\nStudent visa\nEnrolment\nInternational Orientation\nFAQs\nScholarships FAQ\nArriving\nGetting ready to study in Australia? Find out more about what to do to prepare before you leave, how to accept your offer, and what to do when you arrive.\nPreparing to arrive\nWhat to bring\nBringing your family\nHealth cover\nEntering Australia and airport arrival\nBooking an airport pickup\nTips for the best uni life\nAccommodation\nExplore Accommodation Options\nUnder 18s\nAccommodation Scholarships\nCost of living\nLife at Western\nWestern has a range of initiatives that gives international students the best chance of success. Get a better idea of what we offer, and what Australia is like.\nHow Western supports you\nStudent support services\nStudent Central\nStudent Wellbeing\nDisability Service\nSports\nFood on campus\nLife in Australia\nClimate\nCulture\nSafety in Sydney\nSetting up your life\nShopping and food\nUtilities\nTransport\nManaging your money\nWorking in Australia\nCareers and Advice for International Students\nLife Beyond\nWestern\'s contribution to your success does not end at graduation. We have what it takes to support your continuous learning and professional development.\nScholarships valued up to 50% of tuition fees.\nWhen you apply for a coursework program with Western Sydney University you will automatically be considered for an international scholarship. A separate application is not necessary.\nUndergraduate\nPostgraduate\nSustainable Development Goals\nPackaged Offers\nResearch\nExternal Scholarships\nScholarship Frequently Asked Questions\n1 on 1 Scholarship Advising Session\nWestern Sydney University has a range of scholarships available for international students seeking admission to undergraduate programs.\nScholarships valued at $6,000, $3,000 or 50% of tuition fees are awarded on academic merit.\nRegional Achievement Award\nInternational applicants from North Asia and South East Asia are eligible for either a AUD $5,000 or AUD $10,000 Regional Achievement Award, available for all 2026 intakes.\nA $10,000 multi-year scholarship is awarded on the basis of academic merit as recognised by Western Sydney University for admission.\nVice-Chancellor\'s Academic Excellence Undergraduate Scholarships\nWestern Sydney University has a range of scholarships available for international students seeking admission to postgraduate programs.\nVice-Chancellor\'s Academic Excellence Postgraduate Scholarships\nThis Scholarship for Postgraduate international applicants recognises academic merit and offers a $6000 multi-year or $3000 multi-year partial scholarship to be applied towards tuition fees up to a maximum of two years.\nAlumni - International Scholarships\nThe scholarship is available across most undergraduate and postgraduate programs, with some exclusions, and is awarded on a first-come-first-served basis until filled.\napply\nWestern Sydney University International Alumni Scholarship\nSustainable Development Goals - International Scholarships\nThese scholarships have been introduced to support Western Sydney University’s commitment to the United Nations Sustainable Development Goals.\nWestern Sydney University has been named number one in the world for its social, ecological and economic impact in the latest Times Higher Education (THE) University Impact Ranking, 2025.\nSustainable Development Goals - International Undergraduate Scholarship\nSustainable Development Goals - International Postgraduate Scholarship\nWestern Sydney University Vietnam\nAUS Access Scholarship\nWestern Sydney University is offering the AUS Access Scholarship to eligible undergraduate and postgraduate students at our Western Sydney University Vietnam.\nWestern Sydney International EAP Scholarship\nThis Scholarship is for students with an eligible EAP packaged offer and provides a 20% discount on EAP fees for those commencing in 2026.\nJoint Scholarships\nChina Scholarship Council (CSC) Research Scholarship\nGraduate Research School Scholarships\nMain Round Scholarships\nProject Scholarships\nAustralia Awards Scholarship\nScholarship Value\nApplication Process\nAusaid participating countries page\nAccommodation Scholarship\nAccommodation Scholarships are available for International students commencing their studies at Western Sydney University. Visit our Accommodation Scholarship webpage for more information.\nScholarship FAQs\nFrequently Asked Questions\nI have been awarded a scholarship, can I pay a reduced acceptance deposit by deducting the scholarship value?\nTable below (Full Time Study Load) illustrates the Study Period in which Scholarship Recipients who are enrolled in a Full Time Study Load (40 Credit Points per Study Period) may expect to pay less Program Tuition Fees (PTF).\nWestern Sydney University International Scholarship – Undergraduate\nINTAKE\n1ST SCHOLARSHIP PAYMENT\nSTUDY PERIOD WITH REDUCED PTF PAYABLE\n2ND SCHOLARSHIP PAYMENT\n3RD SCHOLARSHIP PAYMENT\nAutumn (Feb) intake\nBy 15 June of first year\nSpring Term\nBy 15 June of second year\nBy 15 June of third year\nSpring (Jul) Intake\nBy 15 December of first year\nAutumn Term\nBy 15 December of second year\nBy 15 December of third year\nWestern Sydney International Scholarship - Postgraduate\nQuarter 1 intake\nBy 15 May of first year\nQuarter 3 Term\nBy 15 May of second year\nQuarter 2 intake\nBy 15 August of first year\nQuarter 4 Term\nBy 15 August of second year\nQuarter 3 intake\nBy 15 November of first year\nQuarter 1 Term\nBy 15 November of second year\nQuarter 4 intake\nBy 15 March of first year\nQuarter 2 Term\nBy 15 March of second year\nQuarrter 2 Term\nWhat is the census date?\nhere\nThis is my second session, but my scholarship value is not showing up on my invoice.\nI need to pay my tuition fee, but my scholarship value is not showing up on my invoice.\nThe fee amount shown on the Letter of Offer for admission is the indicative annual tuition fee. The University reserves the rights to increase tuition fees each year.\nCan I receive cash from my scholarship?\nThe University reserves the rights to reverse all unspent scholarship value recorded in the student’s Fee Account.\nScholarship will be terminated if there is no evidence to show the student has been granted approval for a Leave of Absence.\nWho can I contact if I have scholarship related questions?\nTo support new international students commencing in any 2024 intake, the University is offering a generous scholarship program. The commencing international 2024 cohort may be awarded multi-year scholarships valued at:\n$3K each year (UG up to 3 years; PG up to 2 years)\n$6k each year\n50% tuition fee each year\nOur Sustainable Development Goals Scholarships have been introduced to support Western Sydney University’s commitment to the United Nations Sustainable Development Goals\nMore information:\nWestern Sydney International UG Scholarships\n$3K|$6K\nVC Academic Excellence UG Scholarships\n50%\nWestern Sydney International PG Scholarships\nVC Academic Excellence PG Scholarships\nI have received a scholarship offer to study at Western in an upcoming intake. Will I still receive my scholarship if I defer my offer to another session?\nTuition Fees: I do not have enough funds to make a full payment to accept my offer. Can I make a part payment of my deposit or can I reduce my study load?\nto submit your deferral request. Please note deferral will only be considered under limited circumstances.\nIf you submit a defer request after the CENSUS date of your session, financial and academic penalty details will apply. Please refer to the\nI am having issues selecting my subjects to complete my enrolment or finalise my timetable. Who can I contact to help me?\nIf you are a commencing student and experiencing any of the following subject selection issues, please contact the Student Services Hub (SSH) on +61 2 9852 5499 or\nfor assistance:\nI don’t know what subjects to enrol in\nI am having technical difficulties with selecting subjects\nMy subject is showing full so I can’t complete my timetable\nMy subject does not appear in the tutorial registration/class timetable system\nCurrently enrolled students experiencing the same issues, can contact the Student Infoline on 1300 668 370 or +61 2 9852 5656 if calling from an International location (Press 4 and Press 2).\nonline handbook\nto find the contact details of the academic advisor for your program.\nI’m trying to select my subjects, but no results are revealed after entering a Subject Code and/or Subject Name. What should I do?\nfor assistance.\nI have enrolled, but I do not know how to create my class timetable?\nOnce you have enrolled, you will need to create your class timetable.\nClass Registration\nIf you have just completed your enrolment, it may take a couple of hours for your subjects to appear in Allocate+. Check back later if they do not show up in Allocate+ immediately after enrolment.\nImportant additional information to do with Class Registration can be viewed on our\nClass Registration page\nIf you require any assistance with creating your class timetable, please contact the Student Services Hub (SSH) on +61 2 9852 5499 or\nemail.\nlearn more\nYour application outcome', 'Terms & Conditions\napply.\nMore about this scholarship\nInternational UAC Scholarship\nWestern Sydney International Scholarships - Undergraduate\nOnly students who wish to discuss something not found within their scholarship terms and conditions will be eligible for a 1 on 1 scholarship advising session.\nRequest scholarship advising session\nStudying at Western\nApplying to Western\nArriving at Western\nFooter links\nAccessibility\nWebsite Feedback\nAdmissions Transparency\nComplaints Unit\nDisclaimer\nPrivacy\nRight to Information\nContact Us\nEmail Us\nWestern Sydney University\nLocked Bag 1797\nPenrith NSW 2751\nFollow Us\nWestern Sydney University Copyright ©\n2004-2026\nABN 53 014 069 881\nTop 50 Universities under 50 years old\nScholarships FAQ | Western Sydney University\nFAQs for Scholarships\nNew International Students\nHow to apply for a scholarship?\nHow are the university scholarships assessed?\nHow do I know I have been awarded an International Scholarship by the university?\nIf I defer my commencement, will I still be eligible to receive my scholarship?\nWhat are my scholarship terms and conditions?\nThe terms and conditions of the university funded international scholarship can be found from the university’s\nInternational Scholarship webpage\n. Please click on “More About This Scholarship” button of the scholarship you are awarded.\nI have accepted WSU Multi-Year Scholarship and I am currently enrolled in my first session. When should I expect to receive my scholarship payment?\nFor the Multi-year scholarships, please refer to Schedule 1 of the scholarship terms and conditions.\nAll Scholarship payments are subject in meeting scholarship terms and conditions.\nAs an international student can I study Summer subjects and if so will this impact my scholarship?\nEnrolling in Summer session will not impact the scholarship as long as full time study load is maintained in the primary sessions (Autumn and Spring).\nHow to check fees and payments?\nYou will be able to check your fees and payment by logging into\nMy Student Records\nand clicking Charges and Payments.\nWhy are the fees charged this year different from the amount shown on my Letter of Offer for admission?\nWhat if I fail to meet the scholarship continuing conditions?\nYou will be placed on a scholarship probation or your scholarship will be terminated.\nWhat is the Academic Progress Requirement of my scholarship?\nMy scholarship has been terminated, if I improve my academic performance, will my scholarship be re-instated?\nNo, your scholarship will not be re-instated if you do not submit a special consideration request with supporting documents within 2 weeks of your scholarship termination.\nWhat is GPA? How is it calculated?\nWestern Sydney University uses a cumulative Grade Point Average (GPA) to measure the academic performance of individual students. GPA calculator can be found here:\nGrade Point Average (GPA) Calculator | Western Sydney University\nI am planning to apply for Leave of Absence, how will this affect my scholarship?\nI am in urgent financial need, will a scholarship help?\nIf you are in dire financial need, please contact the Student Welfare Officer at your campus to inquire about an emergency loan which can provide more immediate financial relief. To find out more information, visit\nFinancial Support | Western Sydney University\nMy enrolment has been discontinued due to non-payment of fees. I am now applying for re-admission, will I receive a scholarship again?\nI have received the first scholarship payment at the end of my first semester, but did not enrol in my second semester. Am I allowed to keep the scholarship payment?\nShould you have further questions, please join our Q&As zoom session held every Monday (1pm to 1:30pm Sydney Time), to receive the information during the session.\nTopic:\nScholarship + Sponsored students FAQs and Q&As session\nJoin Zoom Meeting\nhttps://uws.zoom.us/j/88264048567?pwd=QVc3NTFMc0hZNlphTWpocCtwY2JEZz09\nMeeting ID:\n882 6404 8567\nPassword:\n869960\nFAQs for International Students | Western Sydney University\nInternational Student Applicants\nCommencing or Current Enrolled Students\nApplying to study\nAccepting my offer\nChanging my offer\nFees and Finance\nSelecting subjects\nClass timetable\nReduced Study Load, Leave of Absence, Resignation\nStudent Visa and COE Extensions\nWork and Post Study Work Visa\nOverseas Student Health Cover (OSHC)\nStudent Support\nMeeting New Students and Joining Clubs\nTravel Restrictions and Exemptions\nClasses are starting soon and I am yet to receive my visa – what do I do?\nIf you are waiting for your visa and have concerns about commencing your studies on time please contact International Admissions by sending a request in our\nonline application system\nor email\nIf you do not receive your visa in time, you will need to defer your studies to the next available intake of your program.\nIf I have received my visa can I delay my enrolment and request an extension to begin my program at a later date?\nI have accepted my offer and I have just received my academic results. My results do not meet the conditions stated in my offer letter. What happens now?\nIf you have received your results and do not meet entry requirements, you will be able to:\nDefer your offer to the following intake, to provide you with sufficient time to meet conditions. The fees you have paid will be credited to the next intake.\nOr\nWithdraw your offer and request a refund of the fees you have paid as per the\nInternational Student Fee and Refund Agreement.\nWhat if I do not receive my academic results after I accept my offer?\nIf you do not receive your results at least one week prior to the commencement date of your session as outlined in your Letter of Offer, you will need to request a deferment of your program.\nDeferment\nCan I defer my studies if I have accepted my offer and have not yet enrolled in my program?\nUnder limited circumstances you can defer your offer by writing to\nor send a request via your account in\nour online application system\n. The fees you have paid will be credited to the next intake. Your CoE will be updated to reflect your new commencement date.\nI am a new student. What are the steps to enrol in my program and prepare for study at Western?\nAccept your offer\nActivate your Account\nonce you have accepted your offer and received your Confirmation of Enrolment (eCoE)\nEnrol in your subjects\nSelect your class preferences and build your timetable\nComplete Orientation\nApply for your Student ID Card\nIf you have any questions about these steps, please contact the Student Services Hub on +61 2 9852 5499 or email\ninternationalstudy@westernsydney.edu.au\nI will be commencing my program at Western, can I reduce my study load and enrol in only a few subjects?\nAn international student on a student visa,\nOffer of Admission acceptance form\n(check your offer letter)\nPaid fees in full as outlined on your Offer of Admission\nSupplied evidence that you have met all conditions (if applicable) as outlined on your Offer of Admission\nReceived your Confirmation of Enrolment\nActivated your\nWesternAccount\nbefore you can enrol. You will need to accept your offer, paid the acceptance deposit in full and have met all conditions stated on your Letter of Offer, to be able to activate your account.\nPlease ensure you wait at least 15 minutes for your\nto activate before proceeding to the enrolment stage.\nBefore enrolling, please ensure you have completed all the steps above. If you have questions about the above steps, please contact please contact International Admissions at\nor call +61 2 9685 9280.\nIf you have fulfilled all the above and are still having issues, please contact the Student Services Hub (SSH) on +61 2 9852 5499 or\nemail\n. They will help you through the enrolment process and be able to answer any further questions you may have.\nCan I change my mind and defer my program once enrolled?\nIf I am granted a reduced study load or a leave of absence, what impact has this on my visa?\nYou are expected to complete your study within the timeframe stated on your Confirmation of Enrolment (CoE).\nIf you are unable to complete your study within the expected timeframe due to the following reasons you will need a new CoE:\nAdvanced Standing\nProgram Transfer\nConditional Enrolment – failing subjects\nReduced Study Load\nLeave of Absence\nProgram progression – failing to meet pre/co-requisites/subject unavailability\nPlacement requirements\nDepartment of Home Affairs\nWebsite:\nhttps://immi.homeaffairs.gov.au/\nPhone:\nIn Australia: 131 881\nOutside Australia: +61 2 6196 0196\nCan I resign from my program to study at another institution?\nrelease request\nNew students who commence studying at Western while awaiting an outcome of their visa application and then receive a visa refusal\nmay\nbe eligible for a refund. Terms and conditions apply. Contact International Admissions Opens in new window for information.\nThe Immigration Department\'s advice on student visa application matters is subject to change. Please ensure you visit the\nfor the latest update on visa regulations and policies.\nIf you only have a few subjects to complete for your program and you have received a student visa refusal, please contact your\nWestern Success Advisor\nto discuss.\nCan the University help me with any questions about my visa?\nStudent visas are managed by the Department of Home Affairs, not the University.\nWorking rights and Post Study Work Visa\nCan I work more than 48 hours per fortnight with my student visa?\nThe number of hours a student visa holder is able to work is capped at 48 hours per fortnight.\nInternational students have unlimited work rights out of session (vacation periods).\nIf you hold a student visa (subclass 500) you can work unrestricted hours if:\nYou are studying a masters by research or a doctorate degree and have started your program. OR\nThe work is a registered part of your program.\nPlease note:\nfor ongoing support via your smartphone. TalkCampus is a 24/7 global peer support network for international students.\nI’m struggling with my study and home life? Who can I talk to?\nWe care and we’re here to support you.\nIf your main concerns are about your study, you can talk to your program advisor, get\nexpert help via our Study Smart and MESH services\nor visit the\nLibrary website\nfor more information on resources and services available.\nPlease be assured, all information is treated with the strictest confidence. If you are not sure who to contact, reach out to the\nand they will provide you with support and a referral to appropriate services.\nI’d like to enhance my English skills and meet new people. What programs can I join?\nEnglish Conversation Groups\nI need help with my academic studies. What programs are available?\nThe College\nTypes of offer\nResponding to your offer\nTo respond to your offer, follow the instructions in your offer letter. Prior to accepting, please carefully read\nInternational Fee and Refund Agreement\nand\n. Use the program code on your offer letter to learn more about your program\nPaying your fees\nYour fees can be paid by:\nInternational Telegraphic Transfer via Convera\nCredit card via the university\'s online payment system, Payments.\nFlywire\nYou’ll find more information\nStudent visas', 0),
(148, 'Western Sydney University International Alumni Scholarship', 'Multi-year scholarship for international alumni who have previously completed a program at WSU, automatically applied.', 10000.00, 'FIXED', '2026-12-31', 86, 'https://www.westernsydney.edu.au/international/applying/fees-and-costs/scholarships/international-alumni-scholarship', 'active', '2026-01-19 10:39:48', '2026-02-17 03:05:59', NULL, 'Other', 'Applicants must meet the following minimum criteria to be considered for the scholarship: · be an international student and not an Australian citizen, New Zealand citizen or permanent resident of Australia. · commence a new program of study in 2025. · Excludes international students entering Western Sydney University undergraduate programs via the International College or The College pathways. · Any CRICOS registered undergraduate degree (excluding the Bachelor of Clinical Science (Medicine)/Doctor of Medicine, Bachelor of Nursing and Bachelor of Physiotherapy).[1]', NULL, NULL, 0),
(150, 'University of Sydney Vice-Chancellor\'s International Scholarships Scheme', 'Merit-based scholarship for exceptional international students commencing undergraduate or postgraduate coursework degrees. Award amounts ($5,000 to $60,000) determined by academic merit ranking. Applied towards tuition fees, paid in two equal semester instalments.', 60000.00, 'FIXED', '2026-03-23', 88, 'https://www.sydney.edu.au/scholarships/e/vice-chancellor-international-scholarships-scheme.html', 'draft', '2026-01-19 10:39:48', '2026-05-14 13:22:32', NULL, 'Merit-Based', '- Be an international student\n- Have applied for but not yet commenced an undergraduate or postgraduate coursework degree at the University of Sydney\n- Secured an Unconditional Offer of Admission by the application deadline\n- Not be in receipt of any other tuition scholarship or sponsorship administered by the University of Sydney, of a value exceeding A$10,000 per annum\n- Have applied for but not yet commenced a bachelor’s degree or a coursework master’s degree that is a CRICOS registered award program\nNOTE: Applicants commencing a second degree at the University of Sydney are eligible provided they have not previously held the Vice Chancellor’s International Scholarships.', NULL, NULL, 0),
(152, 'UTS Academic Excellence International Scholarship', '30% tuition fee scholarship for high-performing commencing international students. Awarded automatically based on academic merit for undergraduate or postgraduate coursework programs. Applied towards tuition fees for standard course duration.', 0.30, 'PERCENTAGE', '2026-12-31', 89, 'https://www.uts.edu.au/for-students/admissions-entry/scholarships/scholarships-search/uts-academic-excellence-international-scholarship', 'active', '2026-01-19 10:39:48', '2026-04-11 10:05:21', 'stem', 'Merit-Based', 'To be eligible for the Scholarship, an applicant must meet all of the following criteria: Remain an international student (not an Australian citizen, New Zealand citizen or permanent resident of Australia); and Meet all admission requirements for the selected UTS undergraduate or postgraduate coursework program; and For undergraduate coursework admission, completed an Australian Year 12 or UTS recognised high school studies comparable to an Australian Year 12 or an Australian Foundation Studies program, and be admitted to UTS based on this qualification; or For Honours course admission, completed a UTS recognised bachelor degree and be admitted to UTS based on this qualification; or For postgraduate coursework admission, the most recently completed and UTS recognised tertiary qualification at an Australian Bachelor degree level or higher or the Graduate Management Admission Test (GMAT Exam) or the Graduate Record Examination (GRE General Test) (both tests accepted for admission into UTS Business School programs only), and be admitted to UTS based on this qualification; and Commence full-time and on campus (Sydney); and Must not: Be studying a UTS online degree or distance degree; or Complete an approved external articulation or pathway program from an institution outside of Australia; or Be a recipient of other UTS scholarships or grants or the UTS Alumni Advantage Program for the duration of this Scholarship and be a government sponsored student.', NULL, NULL, 0),
(153, 'University of Newcastle International Excellence Scholarship', 'Merit-based scholarship providing 20% annual tuition fee reduction (maximum $24,000 over 4-year degree). Awarded automatically to high-performing international students commencing undergraduate or postgraduate coursework. Applied as tuition fee waiver each term.', 24000.00, 'FIXED', '2026-02-28', 90, 'https://www.newcastle.edu.au/scholarships/UNI_053', 'draft', '2026-01-19 10:39:48', '2026-05-14 13:22:32', NULL, 'Merit-Based', '• Be an International full-fee paying student.\n• Be commencing study in an eligible CRICOS-registered undergraduate or postgraduate coursework degree priority program at the university.\n• Not be the beneficiary of a separate University scholarship unless prior approval for special dispensation has been obtained from the university.\n• Be able to meet the financial obligations of a full fee-paying international student specified by the Australian Government. Evidence of this ability must be provided if requested by the university.\n• Not be studying ELBP, Enabling, Non-Award, Study Abroad or Exchange, Higher Degrees by Research, or some excluded quota-limited programs.\n• Not be studying at offshore campuses, via online delivery, sponsored by an external entity or Australia Awards Scholarship, or transferring from the University\'s Singapore campus.\n• Maintain a Grade Point Average (GPA) of at least 4.0 throughout enrolment.', NULL, NULL, 0),
(154, 'WSU Undergraduate Smooth Start Scholarship', 'Multi-year partial scholarship for new international undergraduate students. Award amount ($3,000 or $6,000 per year) is determined by your academic achievement in Year 12 or equivalent qualification. Applied towards tuition fees for up to three years.', 6000.00, 'FIXED', '2026-12-31', 86, 'https://www.westernsydney.edu.au/international/applying/fees-and-costs/scholarships/international-scholarships-undergraduate', 'active', '2026-01-19 10:39:48', '2026-02-24 02:51:44', NULL, 'Merit-Based', 'be an international student and not an Australian citizen, New Zealand citizen or permanent resident of Australia. If your visa status changes to one of these during the study period, the scholarship will discontinue; commence a new program of study in 2025 for the first time; be applying to study in a CRICOS registered undergraduate degree program; satisfy the academic eligibility requirements for either the $6,000 or $3,000 multi-year scholarship; satisfy all other admission requirements and accept their Offer of Admission letter.', '$3,000-$6,000 per year based on academic merit', NULL, 0),
(155, 'WSU Postgraduate Academic Merit Scholarship', 'Multi-year partial scholarship for new international postgraduate students. Award amount ($3,000 or $6,000 per year) is determined by your academic merit in most recent completed tertiary qualification. Applied towards tuition fees for up to two years.', 6000.00, 'FIXED', '2026-12-31', 86, 'https://www.westernsydney.edu.au/international/applying/fees-and-costs/scholarships/international-scholarships-postgraduate', 'active', '2026-01-19 10:39:48', '2026-02-24 02:51:44', 'stem', 'Merit-Based', 'be an international student and not an Australian citizen, New Zealand citizen or permanent resident of Australia. If your visa status changes to one of these during the study period, the scholarship will discontinue; commence a new program of study in 2025 for the first time; be applying to study in a CRICOS registered undergraduate degree program; satisfy the academic eligibility requirements for either the $6,000 or $3,000 multi-year scholarship; satisfy all other admission requirements and accept their Offer of Admission letter.', '$3,000-$6,000 per year based on academic merit', NULL, 0),
(156, 'UTS Academic Merit International Scholarship', '15% tuition fee scholarship for commencing international students (excluding South Asia). Awarded automatically based on academic merit for undergraduate or postgraduate coursework programs. Applied towards tuition fees for standard course duration.', 0.15, 'PERCENTAGE', '2026-12-31', 89, 'https://www.uts.edu.au/for-students/admissions-entry/scholarships/uts-academic-merit-international-scholarship', 'active', '2026-01-19 10:39:48', '2026-04-11 09:25:52', 'stem', 'Merit-Based', 'UTS Academic Merit International Scholarship\nVALUE\n20% of UTS Tuition Fees (commencing in 2025 intakes), 15% of UTS Tuition Fees (commencing in 2026 intakes)\nApplication Open\n15/07/2024\nDURATION\nThe standard number of credit points required for course.\nSTATUS\nOpen\nOverview\nTo support commencing international students who wish to undertake an undergraduate or postgraduate coursework program at UTS in Sydney.\nWho is eligible\nTo be eligible for the Scholarship, an applicant must meet all of the following criteria:\nRemain an international student (not an Australian citizen, New Zealand citizen or permanent resident of Australia); and\nMeet all admission requirements for the selected UTS undergraduate (including Honours programs) or postgraduate coursework program; and\nCommence full-time and on campus (Sydney)\n[1]\n; and\nMust not be:\nStudying a UTS online degree or distance degree; or\nA citizen of a country in the South Asia region; or\nA recipient of other UTS scholarships or grants or the UTS Alumni Advantage Program for the duration of this Scholarship and be a government sponsored student.\nOn campus studies include face-to-face and/or online (remote) learning in all degrees except online degrees and distance mode degrees.\nSelection process\nFor undergraduate admission, academic merit in the qualification used as the basis of admission for entry into the selected UTS undergraduate program.\nFor postgraduate admission, academic merit in the most recently completed and recognised qualification or the Graduate Management Admission Test (GMAT Exam) or Graduate Record Examination (GRE General Test) (both tests accepted for admission into UTS Business School programs only) for entry into the selected postgraduate coursework program.\nOther information\nApplicable to international students applying to commence in 2025 and 2026 intakes.\nHow to apply\nUTS Future Learner Recruitment and Admissions will automatically consider all commencing international students applying for an undergraduate or postgraduate coursework program at UTS in Sydney for this Scholarship. There is no separate scholarship application or documentation in addition to what is required for the course application.\nOffers will be authorised by UTS Future Learner Recruitment and Admissions.\nContact us\nUTS Future Learners Recruitment and Admissions\nPhone: +61 2 9514 1531\nEmail:\nreps@uts.edu.au\nShare\nShare link\nCopy link\nlink\nFacebook\nLinkedIn\nX\nEmail\nLink copied\nQUICKLINKS', NULL, NULL, 0),
(158, 'UTS Diploma to Degree Scholarship for High School Students', '25% tuition fee scholarship for high-achieving Indonesian and Vietnamese students completing UTS College Diploma pathway. Supports transition from Diploma to undergraduate degree. Awarded automatically based on pathway completion.', 0.25, 'PERCENTAGE', '2026-12-31', 89, 'https://www.uts.edu.au/for-students/admissions-entry/scholarships/uts-diploma-degree-scholarship-high-school-graduates', 'active', '2026-01-19 10:39:48', '2026-04-10 06:41:58', NULL, 'Merit-Based', 'The UTS Academic Excellence International Scholarship supports high-achieving international students beginning their coursework degree in Sydney. To be eligible, applicants must:\n- Remain an international student (not an Australian citizen, New Zealand citizen or permanent resident of Australia);\n- Meet all admission requirements for the selected UTS undergraduate or postgraduate coursework program;\n- For undergraduate coursework admission, completed an Australian Year 12 or UTS recognised high school studies comparable to an Australian Year 12 or an Australian Foundation Studies program;\n- Commence full-time and on campus (Sydney);\n- Must not be studying a UTS online degree or distance degree; or be a recipient of other UTS scholarships or grants.[3][7]', NULL, NULL, 0),
(159, 'UTS Scholarship for European Undergraduate Students', '40% tuition fee scholarship for commencing international students from Europe. Awarded automatically to eligible European students enrolling in undergraduate coursework programs. Applied towards tuition fees for standard course duration.', 0.40, 'PERCENTAGE', '2026-12-31', 89, 'https://www.uts.edu.au/for-students/admissions-entry/scholarships/scholarships-search/uts-scholarship-for-european-undergraduate-students', 'active', '2026-01-19 10:39:48', '2026-04-11 10:04:55', NULL, 'Other', 'To be eligible for the Scholarship, an applicant must meet all of the following criteria: Remain an international student (not an Australian citizen, New Zealand citizen or permanent resident of Australia); and Be a citizen of a country in the European region; and Commence full-time studies and on campus at UTS; and Meet UTS admission criteria for the selected UTS undergraduate coursework program; and Must not: be studying a UTS online degree or distance mode degree; or be based in Australia (must be based offshore) prior to commencement at UTS, or be a recipient of other UTS International scholarships or grants or the UTS Alumni Advantage Program for the duration of this Scholarship; and be a government sponsored student.', NULL, NULL, 0),
(160, 'UTS Scholarship for Gaokao Students from China', 'Tiered tuition fee scholarship (50-75%) for top-achieving Chinese students admitted based on Gaokao results. Award level determined by academic merit ranking. Awarded automatically to eligible students commencing undergraduate programs. Maximum duration of eight sessions.', 0.75, 'PERCENTAGE', '2026-12-31', 89, 'https://www.uts.edu.au/for-students/admissions-entry/scholarships/scholarships-search/scholarship-for-gaokao-students-from-peoples-republic-of-china', 'active', '2026-01-19 10:39:48', '2026-04-11 10:05:04', NULL, 'Merit-Based', 'To be eligible to apply for the Scholarship, an applicant must meet all the following criteria: Must be an international student (not an Australian citizen, New Zealand citizen or permanent resident of Australia); and Must have completed Senior Secondary School (Gao San) in China and undertaken the Gaokao administrated by Provincial or Municipal Education Examination Authority, China; and Must meet all UTS admission criteria for the selected UTS undergraduate degree course; and Must have completed the Gaokao with a competitive score, no longer than one year prior to commencing at UTS, and be admitted based on this qualification to UTS; and Must commence full-time and on-campus (Sydney); and Must not: be studying a UTS online degree or distance degree; or be a government sponsored student; or be a recipient of another UTS scholarship for the duration of this Scholarship.', NULL, NULL, 0),
(161, 'UTS Southeast Asia International Scholarship', '20% tuition fee scholarship for commencing international students from Southeast Asia. Awarded automatically based on academic merit for undergraduate or postgraduate coursework programs. Applied towards tuition fees for standard course duration.', 0.20, 'PERCENTAGE', '2026-12-31', 89, 'https://www.uts.edu.au/for-students/admissions-entry/scholarships/uts-southeast-asia-international-scholarship', 'active', '2026-01-19 10:39:48', '2026-04-11 09:26:11', NULL, 'Merit-Based', 'UTS Southeast Asia International Scholarship\nVALUE\n20% of tuition fees\nApplication Open\n12/12/2025\nApplication Close\n31/12/2028\nDURATION\nThe duration of the Scholarship is the standard number of credit points required for completion of the Recipient\'s enrolled undergraduate course up to a maximum of ten (10) sessions under any program or postgraduate course up to a maximum of four (4) sessions under any program.\nSTATUS\nOpen\nOverview\nTo support commencing international students from Southeast Asia who wish to undertake an undergraduate or postgraduate coursework program at UTS in Sydney.\nWho is eligible\nTo be eligible for the Scholarship, an applicant must meet all of the following criteria:\nRemain an international student (not an Australian citizen, New Zealand citizen or permanent resident of Australia); and\nBe a citizen of one of the following countries in the Southeast Asia region:\nBrunei; or\nCambodia; or\nIndonesia; or\nLaos; or\nMalaysia; or\nPhilippines; or\nSingapore; or\nThailand; or\nTimor-Leste; or\nVietnam; and\nMeet all admission requirements for the selected UTS undergraduate (including Honours programs) or postgraduate coursework program; and\nCommencing full-time and on campus (Sydney)\n[1]\n;\nBe admitted into an UTS coursework intake between Spring session 2026 to Summer session 2028; and\nMust not be:\nStudying a UTS online degree or distance degree; or\nA recipient of other UTS scholarships or grants or the UTS Alumni Advantage Program for the duration of this Scholarship and be a government sponsored student.\nOn campus studies include face-to-face and/or online (remote) learning in all degrees except online degrees and distance mode degrees.\nSelection process\nFor undergraduate admission, academic merit in the qualification used as the basis of admission for entry into the selected UTS undergraduate program.\nFor postgraduate admission, academic merit in the most recently completed and recognised qualification or the Graduate Management Admission Test (GMAT Exam) or Graduate Record Examination (GRE General Test) (both tests accepted for admission into UTS Business School programs only) for entry into the selected postgraduate coursework program.\nOther information\nUTS\nwill automatically consider from Spring session 2026 to Summer session 2028 intake\nall commencing international students applying for an undergraduate or postgraduate coursework program at UTS in Sydney for this Scholarship. There is no separate scholarship application or documentation in addition to what is required for the course application.\nOffers will be authorised by Head of Admissions Services and Scholarships, UTS Future Learner Recruitment and Admissions.\nContact us\nUTS Future Learners Recruitment and Admissions\nPhone: +61 2 9514 1531\nEmail:\nreps@uts.edu.au\nUTS International Website:\nhttp://uts.edu.au/international\nShare\nShare link\nCopy link\nlink\nFacebook\nLinkedIn\nX\nEmail\nLink copied\nQUICKLINKS', NULL, NULL, 0),
(183, 'UTS Vingroup Scholarships', 'Full scholarship for Vietnamese students pursuing Masters or PhD in Engineering and IT. Awarded by Vingroup Science & Technology Scholarship Program for research with potential to create breakthroughs in Vietnam. Separate application required through Vingroup/VinUniversity.', 20000.00, 'FIXED', '2026-02-28', 89, 'https://scholarships.vinuni.edu.vn/', 'draft', '2026-01-19 10:43:45', '2026-05-14 13:22:32', 'other', 'Merit-Based', '- Remain an international student (not an Australian citizen, New Zealand citizen or permanent resident of Australia).\n- The UTS Academic Excellence International Scholarship supports high-achieving international students beginning their coursework degree in Sydney.\n- Country and region-specific scholarships with eligibility tied to specific nationalities/regions (e.g., South Asia, Southeast Asia, Vietnam, Latin America, Africa).', NULL, NULL, 1),
(185, 'UNSW International Student Award', '20% tuition fee scholarship for commencing international students. Merit-based award for undergraduate or postgraduate coursework programs. Applied as contribution towards tuition fees for duration of standard program.', 0.20, 'PERCENTAGE', '2026-02-26', 91, 'https://www.scholarships.unsw.edu.au/international-student-award', 'draft', '2026-01-19 10:45:08', '2026-05-14 13:22:32', 'stem', 'Merit-Based', 'To be eligible, applicants must meet all of the following criteria:\nBe an International Student; and\nBe a citizen of an eligible country; and\nBe commencing full-time study as a new student on campus^ in a UNSW Diploma, UNSW Undergraduate or Postgraduate coursework program (excluding programs offered by AGSM, UNSW Online, UNSW Canberra, UNSW Foundation Programs, Transition Program Online, any program taught in the Hexamester calendar or Study Abroad students); and\nMust have applied and received an offer of admission* into a UNSW undergraduate or postgraduate degree program; and\nMust not be a current student of UNSW (exceptions made for those who have completed an undergraduate program at UNSW and are commencing a postgraduate program)', NULL, NULL, 0),
(218, 'Vice-Chancellor\'s International Scholarships Scheme', 'Merit-based scholarship for exceptional international students commencing undergraduate or postgraduate coursework degrees. Five tiers ranging from $5,000 to $60,000 awarded based on academic achievement. Automatically considered upon admission.', 40000.00, 'FIXED', '2026-12-31', 88, 'https://www.sydney.edu.au/scholarships/e/vice-chancellor-international-scholarships-scheme.html', 'active', '2026-02-18 10:59:45', '2026-02-23 22:16:29', NULL, 'Merit-Based', '- Be an international student as defined in the Higher Education Support Act 2003\r\n- Have applied for but not yet commenced an undergraduate or postgraduate coursework degree at the University of Sydney\r\n- Not be an Australian or New Zealand citizen\r\n- Not be a recipient of scholarships provided by the Australian Government\r\n- Maintain a minimum semester average mark (SAM) of 65 each semester\r\n- Enroll full-time in your degree', NULL, NULL, 0),
(219, 'Sydney International Student Award', '20% tuition fee reduction for the duration of undergraduate or postgraduate coursework degrees. Open to students from select countries including Africa, South/Central America, Central Asia, Eastern Europe, and specific Asian countries. Requires personal statement.', 0.20, 'PERCENTAGE', '2026-12-31', 88, 'https://www.sydney.edu.au/study/fees-and-loans/scholarships/sydney-international-student-award.html', 'active', '2026-02-18 10:59:45', '2026-05-03 01:38:19', NULL, 'Other', '- Be an international student (not Australian or New Zealand citizen or permanent resident)\r\n- Hold citizenship of one of the eligible countries: Africa, South & Central America, Central Asia, Eastern Europe, Bangladesh, Cambodia, India, Indonesia, Japan, Malaysia, Mongolia, Myanmar, Nepal, Pakistan, Philippines, South Korea, Sri Lanka, Thailand, Turkey, Vietnam\r\n- Receive admission into a full-time undergraduate or postgraduate coursework degree, commencing in 2026\r\n- Not have already started a degree at the University of Sydney (however, you are eligible if completing a degree and applying for a second degree)\r\n- Complete a personal statement as part of your application (maximum 200 words per section)', NULL, NULL, 0);
INSERT INTO `scholarships` (`id`, `title`, `description`, `amount`, `amount_type`, `deadline`, `organization_id`, `application_url`, `status`, `created_at`, `updated_at`, `industry`, `scholarship_type`, `eligibility_raw_text`, `benefits_text`, `conditions_text`, `requires_application`) VALUES
(220, 'Sydney International Undergraduate Academic Excellence Scholarship', 'Full tuition fees and Student Services Amenities Fee for exceptional international undergraduate students from priority markets. Covers the published full-time duration up to 4 years. Approximately 20 scholarships awarded annually. Applications for 2026 are now closed.', 0.00, 'FIXED', '2026-12-31', 88, 'https://www.sydney.edu.au/scholarships/e/sydney-international-undergraduate-academic-excellence-scholarship.html', 'active', '2026-02-18 10:59:45', '2026-05-03 01:38:19', NULL, 'Merit-Based', 'University_\nSydney International Undergraduate Academic Excellence Scholarship\nAn undergraduate scholarship\nAn undergraduate scholarship to support exceptional international students from diverse priority markets study across diverse undergraduate courses at the University of Sydney.\nHighlights\nValue\nEligibility\nOpen date\nClose date\n100% tuition fees and SSAF for the published full-time duration of\nthe recipient’s single undergraduate degree\nInternational student\nApplied for but not yet commenced a single undergraduate coursework degree\nCurrently closed\nHow to apply\nPlease note that applications for 2026 are closed.\nOnly successful applicants will be contacted after applying for the scholarship. The indicative turnaround time to receive a scholarship offer is 5 weeks from when you submit an application for the scholarship.\nApproximately 20 scholarships will be awarded globally per year across the two intakes focusing on diversity of course and diversity of nationality. The information listed here is subject to change without notice. Information describing the number and value of scholarships awarded is indicative.\nBenefits\nThe scholarship will provide the below benefits for the published full-time duration of the recipient’s single undergraduate degree (including embedded honours) up to a maximum total duration of 4 years full-time study.\n100% tuition fees, and\nStudent Services Amenities Fee.\nNo other amount is payable. Recipients are responsible for all other costs for studying at the University of Sydney including but not limited to, Overseas Health Cover (OSHC), living costs, accommodation, textbooks, flights and costs associated with being under the age of 18.\nWho\'s eligible\nYou must:\nhave applied for but not yet commenced a single undergraduate coursework degree (may include embedded honours) at the University of Sydney at the time of award which has a maximum duration of 4 years. Only applicants who apply for eligible courses will be considered for this scholarship. The scholarship is not available for combined degrees with a postgraduate component, the Bachelor of Arts (Dual Degree, Sciences Po, France), Bachelor of Economics (Dual Degree, Sciences Po, France) and degrees that include the Bachelor of Advanced Studies. *\nmust enrol in their eligible degree full-time\nnot be commencing a second degree at the University of Sydney\nbe an international student as defined in the Higher Education Support Act 2003. Australian Citizens, Australian Permanent Residents and dual citizens with Australian nationality are not eligible\nmust have completed secondary school (or a foundation program in Australia or from a University of Sydney recognised foundation partner)\nmust not have previously undertaken any tertiary studies (excluding extension studies completed as part of a year 12 program).\n* For more information about undergraduate admissions entry requirements and eligibility for the Sydney International Undergraduate Academic Excellent Scholarship from your country and type of high school qualifications recognised, please contact our\nregional experts\n.\nBackground\nThe scholarship was established to support exceptional international students from diverse priority markets study across diverse undergraduate courses at the University of Sydney.\nTerms and Conditions\n1. Background\na. The Sydney International Undergraduate Academic Excellence Scholarship was established in 2024 to support exceptional international students from diverse priority markets study across diverse undergraduate courses at the University of Sydney.\n2. Eligibility\na. Applicants must have applied for but not yet commenced a single undergraduate coursework degree (may include embedded honours) at the University of Sydney at the time of award which has a maximum duration of 4 years.\nb. Only applicants who apply for eligible courses will be considered for this scholarship. The scholarship is not available for combined degrees with a postgraduate component, the Bachelor', 'Full tuition fees + SSAF (up to 4 years)', NULL, 1),
(221, 'Business School International Scholarship', 'Merit-based scholarship for international students commencing postgraduate Business School degrees (excluding MBA programs). Awards of $10,000 or $5,000 for one semester based on academic merit. Automatically considered during admission. Not offered in Semester 1 2026.', 10000.00, 'FIXED', '2026-07-31', 88, 'https://www.sydney.edu.au/scholarships/a/international-scholarship.html', 'active', '2026-02-18 10:59:45', '2026-04-11 09:26:04', NULL, 'Merit-Based', 'University_\nBusiness School International Scholarship\nA University of Sydney Business School scholarship\nUp to $10,000 scholarship awarded to international students commencing a second degree at a master\'s level at the University of Sydney Business School in the next semester of study.\nHighlights\nValue\nEligibility\nOpen date\nClose date\n$5,000 to $10,000\nInternational student\nhave completed a degree at the University of Sydney, and hold an Unconditional offer for a Master\'s by coursework program (excluding MBA, MBA Leadership and Enterprise, Executive MBA, and Master of Management (CEMS))\nN/A\nHow to apply\nNo separate application required. Students are automatically considered for this scholarship during the admission process.\nNote: This scholarship will not be offered in Semester 1 2026.\nBenefits\nThe amounts are offered based on ranking against selection criteria:\n$10,000 fee credit for one semester\n$5,000 fee credit for one semester\nThe allocation of scholarships will be determined by the Business School’s Coursework Scholarships Sub-Committee.\nWho is eligible\nYou must:\nbe an international student\nhave completed a degree at the University of Sydney in the teaching period immediately prior to the semester for which the scholarship offer is made.\nnot have previously held the same scholarship.\nBackground\nBusiness School International Scholarships are awarded to international students of high academic merit completing degrees at the University of Sydney. The scholarship is open to commencing postgraduate international students who have received an offer of admission for a full-time coursework degree at the University of Sydney Business School.\nTerms and conditions\n1. Background\nBusiness School International Scholarships are awarded to international students of high academic merit enrolling into degrees at the University of Sydney. The scholarship is open to commencing postgraduate international students who have received a conditional or unconditional offer of admission for a coursework full-time degree at the University of Sydney Business School.\n2. Eligibility\na. To be eligible for the Scholarship, recipients must be an international student as defined in the Higher Education Support Act 2003 at the time of consideration.\nb. The recipient must have completed a qualification at an Australian university in the two years immediately prior to the semester for which the scholarship offer is made or be a high merit applicant with a qualification obtained from a University outside of Australia.\nd. Recipients may not have previously received a Business School International Scholarship.\ne. The Scholarship may be held concurrently with other Scholarships and Awards offered by the University of Sydney or by an external provider.\n3. Selection Criteria\na. The Scholarship will be awarded to commencing students based on academic merit as assessed from a student’s application for admission.\nb. The Scholarship will be awarded on the nomination of a selection committee consisting of two members of the Business School’s Coursework Scholarships Sub-Committee.\n4. Value\na. Two scholarship amounts are offered based on ranking against selection criteria:\nI. $10,000 payable for one semester to commencing students of exceptional academic merit\nII. $5,000 payable for one semester to commencing students of very high academic merit.\nThe overall number of scholarships will be determined by the Coursework Scholarships SubCommittee and subject to availability of funds.\nb. Recipients must return a signed copy of the acceptance of their scholarship offer by the nominated deadline stated in the scholarship offer notification.\nc. Recipients must enrol in the Eligible Course as per clause 2c of this document and remain enrolled after census date to receive payment.\nd. The payment will be made as a credit to the recipient’s Student Fee Account after the census date of each semester. The credit can be used to offset tuition fee in the following semester. The credit c', NULL, NULL, 0),
(222, 'Research Training Program (RTP) - International', 'Australian Government scholarship providing tuition fees, living stipend ($42,754 p.a. for 2025), and other allowances for international postgraduate research students (PhD or Master by Research). Highly competitive merit-based selection.', 42754.00, 'FIXED', '2026-09-11', 88, 'https://www.sydney.edu.au/scholarships/australian-government-research-training-program/rtp-international.html', 'active', '2026-02-18 10:59:45', '2026-04-10 06:41:58', NULL, 'Merit-Based', '- Be an international student\r\n- Have an unconditional offer or be enrolled in master by research or PhD at University of Sydney\r\n- Demonstrate outstanding academic achievement and research potential\r\n- Submit scholarship application form by deadlines\r\n\r\nDeadlines: 11 September 2026 (research periods 1-2), 18 December 2026 (research periods 3-4)', NULL, NULL, 1),
(223, 'GW-NSW Education Trust Award', 'Merit-based award for women in their third year of full-time undergraduate study at NSW or ACT universities. Up to $5,000 awarded annually to students with good academic records (minimum Credit average) who plan to continue further study.', 5000.00, 'FIXED', '2027-03-05', 92, 'https://gwnsw.org.au/the-education-trust-award/', 'active', '2026-02-23 21:28:19', '2026-05-14 12:38:33', NULL, 'Merit-Based', '- Be female\r\n- In third year of full-time undergraduate course at a university in NSW or ACT (having completed two years)\r\n- Have good academic record (minimum Credit average)\r\n- Be an Australian citizen or permanent resident\r\n- Possibly planning to proceed to honours\r\n- Preference given to on-campus students, but full-time online students also eligible\r\n- Preference given to those with plans for further study', NULL, NULL, 1),
(224, 'Joan Bielski Scholarship', 'Need-based scholarship for mature-age women (35+) commencing their first university degree. Provides $12,000 per annum for up to three years to women who experienced hardship and could not attend university earlier. Named after feminist Joan Bielski AO.', 12000.00, 'FIXED', '2027-04-02', 92, 'https://gwnsw.org.au/joan-bielski-scholarship-1st-year-mature-age-women-students-commencing-their-first-degree/', 'active', '2026-02-23 21:28:19', '2026-05-14 12:38:33', NULL, 'Need-Based', '- Be female\r\n- Aged 35 years or over at time of application\r\n- First-year undergraduate student in full-time study or equivalent\r\n- Enrolled at university in NSW or ACT (Australian Universities\' list)\r\n- Has experienced hardship\r\n- Has valid reason for not commencing university study earlier\r\n- Be an Australian citizen or permanent resident\r\n- Maintain satisfactory academic achievement for renewal', NULL, NULL, 1),
(225, 'Jamieson Award', 'Merit-based award for high-achieving women who completed their first undergraduate degree in 2025 and are proceeding to further study. Up to $5,000 for students with significant community contribution. Preference given to full-time campus students.', 5000.00, 'FIXED', '2027-02-16', 92, 'https://gwnsw.org.au/jamieson-award/', 'active', '2026-02-23 23:02:31', '2026-05-14 12:38:33', NULL, 'Merit-Based', 'High achieving women students who completed the final year of their first undergraduate degree in 2025 at any university listed on the Australian Universities\' list with campuses in NSW or ACT. Students enrolled in double degrees may only apply when the final year of the first degree was completed in 2025. Preference is given to applicants who\'ve made a significant contribution to their community. Preference will be given to applicants who are enrolled full time on campus but applicants who are studying full time or equivalent are also eligible to apply. Must be an Australian citizen or permanent resident of Australia.', NULL, NULL, 1),
(226, 'Joan Ritchie Award', 'Need-based award for mature-age women (25+) in second year of their first undergraduate degree who are experiencing personal disadvantage. $3,500 for students with satisfactory academic record facing financial difficulty, disability, caring responsibilities, or other challenges.', 3500.00, 'FIXED', '2027-04-16', 92, 'https://gwnsw.org.au/joan-ritchie-award/', 'active', '2026-02-23 23:02:31', '2026-05-14 12:38:33', NULL, 'Need-Based', '- Be female\r\n- Aged 25 years or over at time of application\r\n- Completed 1st year of full-time study of first undergraduate degree at university in NSW or ACT\r\n- Satisfactory academic record in first year\r\n- Experiencing personal disadvantage (financial difficulty, low income, ESL, migrant/refugee status, disability, medical condition, family/caring responsibilities, geographical isolation, career/study disruption)\r\n- Be an Australian citizen or permanent resident', NULL, NULL, 1),
(227, 'Tempe Mann Travelling Scholarship', 'Research scholarship for women in 2nd-3rd year of research masters/doctorate at University of Sydney (or first degree/masters from USyd) to conduct short-term research overseas or interstate. Two awards of up to $8,000 each for advanced research or coursework enhancing thesis quality.', 8000.00, 'FIXED', '2027-04-30', 92, 'https://gwnsw.org.au/tempe-mann-travelling-scholarship-guidelines/', 'active', '2026-02-23 23:02:31', '2026-05-14 12:38:33', NULL, 'Merit-Based', '- Be female\r\n- Enrolled as research masters or research doctoral student at University of Sydney, OR have first degree/masters from University of Sydney and enrolled for doctorate at another NSW/ACT university\r\n- In second or third year of research degree\r\n- Have proof of acceptance by university/organisation where research will be conducted\r\n- Establish necessity for overseas or interstate study/research\r\n- Be an Australian citizen or permanent resident\r\n- Short-listed candidates required to attend interview\r\n- Must provide detailed budget justifying requested amount\r\n- Must present written/verbal report at conclusion\r\n- Must acknowledge scholarship in related publications', NULL, NULL, 1),
(229, 'Faculty of Science and Engineering Women in STEM Scholarship', 'Recognising excellence in Science, Information Technology and Engineering, this scholarship funds female-identifying scholars based on excellence and equity to encourage and support careers in STEM.', 5000.00, 'FIXED', '2026-11-23', 93, 'https://www.mq.edu.au/study/admissions-and-entry/scholarships/domestic/faculty-of-science-and-engineering-women-in-stem-scholarship', 'active', '2026-02-26 00:39:15', '2026-02-26 00:39:15', NULL, 'Merit-And-Need', 'Commencing undergraduate or postgraduate coursework in Faculty of Science and Engineering Session 1 2026. Female-identifying student. Full-time and on campus study. Demonstrated high academic achievement. Preference for financial hardship or disadvantage.', NULL, NULL, 1),
(295, 'Gallipoli Scholarship Fund', 'The Gallipoli Scholarship Fund supports descendants of Australian and New Zealand veterans entering their first year of tertiary education. Applicants must demonstrate financial or other hardship (financial, medical, familial, or environmental). Multiple named bursaries are awarded from within the annual pool, sponsored by RSL clubs, corporates, and community donors including the Bill Hall Bursary, Merrylands RSL Bursary, Lockheed Martin Australia Bursary, Calleo Indigenous Bursary, Hall Rotary Club Bursary, EY Bursary, RSL NSW Scholarship, and the Mustafa Kemal Ataturk Memorial Bursary.', 8000.00, 'FIXED', '2026-03-31', 133, 'https://gallipolischolarship.com.au/apply', 'draft', '2026-04-17 11:08:00', '2026-05-14 13:22:32', NULL, 'Need-Based', NULL, NULL, NULL, 1),
(296, 'Lions Nurses\' Scholarship Foundation (NSW/ACT)', 'Annual scholarships available to registered nurses and enrolled nurses in NSW and ACT. Applications open on 1 August and close on 31 October each year.', 0.00, 'FIXED', '2025-10-31', 135, 'https://www.nswnma.asn.au/education/scholarships/', 'draft', '2026-05-03 01:09:54', '2026-05-13 12:15:43', 'Medicine', 'Merit-Based', 'Scholarships\nNSWNMA scholarships\nScholarships and subsidies\nEducation and research scholarships and subsidies are available to nurses and midwives through the Association and other nursing bodies.\nThe following scholarships are administered by the NSWNMA.\nRoz Norman Scholarship\nRoz Norman was an outstanding activist, branch official and Councillor of the NSWNMA and ANMF. In honour of her outstanding contributions, the Roz Norman Scholarship was created to further humanitarian,…\nLearn More\nEdith Cavell Trust Scholarship\nApplications for the Edith Cavell Trust Scholarship open annually on 1 July. Only Members of the NSW Nurses and Midwives’ Association (NSWNMA) are eligible to apply.\nLions Nurses’ Scholarship Foundation (NSW/ACT)\nLions Nurses Scholarships open for application on 1 August and close on 31 October each year*. These are available to any eligible registered nurse or enrolled nurse.\nThe following scholarships are not administered by the NSWNMA.\nFollow the links to find out more about each one and if you have any queries regarding these, contact the administering organisation.\nTLR Foundation Nursing Scholarships\nNSW Health Nursing and Midwifery Scholarship Fund\nNSW Health Tertiary Health Study Subsidies\nAged Care Nursing Scholarship Program\nNSW RDN Health Workforce Scholarship Program\nBush Bursaries and Country Women’s Association Scholarships (for nursing and midwifery students)\nNSW RDN Outreach Student Placement Program (for nursing and midwifery students)\nNSW RDN Go Rural Scholarships (Rural Career Experiences for University Students)\nThe Australian College of Nursing Scholarship Information\nBonnie Boezeman AO Leadership in Nursing Scholarship\nPublic Education Foundation Scholarships\nAustralian Veterans’ Children Assistance Trust Scholarships\nJoan Hardy Scholarship for post-graduate nursing research\nAustralian Government Study Australia\nWomen and Leadership Australia – Healthcare Sector Women’s Leadership Scholarship', NULL, NULL, 1),
(297, 'Federation\'s Future Teacher Scholarships', 'Scholarships worth $4000 offered by the NSW Teachers Federation to students enrolled in NESA-accredited initial teacher education programs in NSW. The funds can be used for educational expenses directly related to teacher training such as laptops, textbooks, computer software and stationery. Up to 15 scholarships are awarded across multiple categories including general applicants, Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander students, rural/remote students, first-year students, and culturally and linguistically diverse students.', 4000.00, 'FIXED', '2026-05-27', 134, 'https://www.nswtf.org.au/news/2026/02/04/applications-now-open-for-federations-4000-future-teacher-scholarships/', 'active', '2026-05-03 01:14:15', '2026-05-13 12:28:06', 'Education', 'Merit-And-Need', 'Federation student members (studying full or part time) may apply for a Future Teacher Scholarship. Students enrolled in NESA-accredited initial teacher education programs in NSW are encouraged to apply. Applicants may nominate for more than one category of scholarship in their application, if appropriate. Past scholarship recipients have proudly attended public schools and demonstrated a strong desire and commitment to work in the public education system.', NULL, NULL, 1),
(298, 'Edith Cavell Scholarship', 'An annual scholarship administered by the NSWNMA with applications opening on 1 July each year. Only members of the NSW Nurses and Midwives\' Association are eligible to apply.', 0.00, 'FIXED', '2026-12-31', 137, 'https://www.nswnma.asn.au/education/scholarships/', 'draft', '2026-05-03 01:14:15', '2026-05-14 11:37:48', 'Medicine', 'Merit-Based', 'Only Members of the NSW Nurses and Midwives\' Association (NSWNMA) are eligible to apply.', NULL, NULL, 1),
(299, 'Roz Norman Scholarship', 'A scholarship created in honour of Roz Norman, an outstanding activist, branch official and Councillor of the NSWNMA and ANMF. The scholarship is designed to further humanitarian contributions in nursing and midwifery.', 0.00, 'FIXED', '2026-12-31', 137, 'https://www.nswnma.asn.au/education/scholarships/', 'draft', '2026-05-03 01:14:15', '2026-05-13 12:15:44', 'Medicine', 'Other', 'Scholarships\nNSWNMA scholarships\nScholarships and subsidies\nEducation and research scholarships and subsidies are available to nurses and midwives through the Association and other nursing bodies.\nThe following scholarships are administered by the NSWNMA.\nRoz Norman Scholarship\nRoz Norman was an outstanding activist, branch official and Councillor of the NSWNMA and ANMF. In honour of her outstanding contributions, the Roz Norman Scholarship was created to further humanitarian,…\nLearn More\nEdith Cavell Trust Scholarship\nApplications for the Edith Cavell Trust Scholarship open annually on 1 July. Only Members of the NSW Nurses and Midwives’ Association (NSWNMA) are eligible to apply.\nLions Nurses’ Scholarship Foundation (NSW/ACT)\nLions Nurses Scholarships open for application on 1 August and close on 31 October each year*. These are available to any eligible registered nurse or enrolled nurse.\nThe following scholarships are not administered by the NSWNMA.\nFollow the links to find out more about each one and if you have any queries regarding these, contact the administering organisation.\nTLR Foundation Nursing Scholarships\nNSW Health Nursing and Midwifery Scholarship Fund\nNSW Health Tertiary Health Study Subsidies\nAged Care Nursing Scholarship Program\nNSW RDN Health Workforce Scholarship Program\nBush Bursaries and Country Women’s Association Scholarships (for nursing and midwifery students)\nNSW RDN Outreach Student Placement Program (for nursing and midwifery students)\nNSW RDN Go Rural Scholarships (Rural Career Experiences for University Students)\nThe Australian College of Nursing Scholarship Information\nBonnie Boezeman AO Leadership in Nursing Scholarship\nPublic Education Foundation Scholarships\nAustralian Veterans’ Children Assistance Trust Scholarships\nJoan Hardy Scholarship for post-graduate nursing research\nAustralian Government Study Australia\nWomen and Leadership Australia – Healthcare Sector Women’s Leadership Scholarship', NULL, NULL, 1),
(300, 'Freemasons Foundation Victoria Scholarship 2026', 'The Freemasons Foundation Victoria Scholarships aim to support access to higher education for undergraduate students facing educational disadvantage and who contribute to their community. Two scholarships valued at $7,500 each are available for one year to first-year commencing students at Swinburne University of Technology in Semester 1, 2026. Applicants must demonstrate community/leadership experience and evidence of educational disadvantage. No Freemasons family connection is required — this scholarship is open to any eligible student based on financial need and community involvement.', 7500.00, 'FIXED', '2026-12-31', 138, 'https://www.swinburne.edu.au/study/options/scholarships/421/freemasons-foundation-victoria-scholarship-2026/', 'active', '2026-05-03 01:14:15', '2026-05-14 12:41:33', NULL, 'Need-Based', 'To be eligible for the Freemasons Foundation Victoria Scholarship, applicants must: Meet the following criteria: an Australian citizen or an Australian permanent resident. Meet the following enrolment criteria: be a first year commencing Swinburne student in Semester 1, 2026. (Preference given to Year 12 school leavers) enrolled full-time in any undergraduate degree or vocational education course offered by Swinburne University of Technology studying on-campus or online Demonstrated community/leadership experience such as through volunteering, sports coaching and/or community service Submit a personal statement (500 words) addressing the following points: interest in your chosen field of study your volunteering/leadership experience in the community how this scholarship would make a difference in your life Provide evidence of educational disadvantage, which may fall under the categories listed below. To assist you, we\'ve included a link to the VTAC website for further guidance on preparing your evidence. Personal information and location Financial hardship Living with a disability or medical condition Difficult family and life circumstances Provide a written reference from a teacher, community leader, or employer. Note: referees cannot be a family member or friend.', NULL, NULL, 1),
(301, 'David Johnson Freemasons Foundation Scholarship 2026', 'This scholarship, established through the generous support of Swinburne alumnus and engineer David Johnson via Freemasons Foundation Victoria, provides financial support to undergraduate engineering students from disadvantaged backgrounds or those required to relocate. The scholarship is valued at $8,000 per year for up to four years and is available to commencing first-year students at Swinburne University of Technology. No Freemasons family connection is required — this scholarship is open to any eligible student based on financial need and community involvement.', 8000.00, 'FIXED', '2026-12-31', 139, 'https://www.swinburne.edu.au/study/options/scholarships/550/david-johnson-freemasons-foundation-scholarship-2026/', 'active', '2026-05-03 01:14:15', '2026-05-14 12:41:33', 'Other', 'Need-Based', 'To be eligible for the David Johnson Freemasons Foundation Scholarship, applicants must: Meet the following criteria: Australian citizen or Australian Permanent Resident Meet the following enrolment criteria: be a commencing first year Swinburne student in Semester 1, 2026 enrolled full-time in an eligible course and major (see courses eligible in section above) enrolled on campus (Hawthorn) Submit a personal statement (500 words) or short video (2 minutes) addressing the following: interest in pursuing a career in engineering educational disadvantage how the scholarship will benefit your studies and support you **If you are submitting a video, please upload your video to cloud based storage and provide the link in a MS Word or PDF document. The video must be accessible by anyone - provide any passwords if necessary. Provide evidence of financial and/or personal disadvantage, or the need to relocate in order to study. Disadvantage(s) may include: financial difficulty or low-socio economic status (Centrelink statement, payslips) disability or medical condition delay or interruption to career or studies because of family responsibilities or illness relocation from a rural or regional area in order to undertake tertiary study English as a second language identification as an Aboriginal or Torres Strait Islander first in family to attend university', NULL, NULL, 1),
(302, 'Freemasons Foundation Scholarship', 'An equity scholarship for domestic students studying full-time at Australian Catholic University\'s Ballarat or Melbourne campuses who live or have lived in a regional, rural or remote location. The scholarship provides $5,000 to support students from disadvantaged geographical areas in their studies. No Freemasons family connection is required — this scholarship is open to any eligible student based on financial need and community involvement.', 5000.00, 'FIXED', '2026-03-01', 136, 'https://www.acu.edu.au/study-at-acu/fees-and-scholarships/find-a-scholarship/freemasons-foundation-scholarship', 'draft', '2026-05-03 01:14:15', '2026-05-13 12:26:54', NULL, 'Need-Based', 'For domestic students studying full-time at the Ballarat or Melbourne campus who live (or have lived) in a regional, rural or remote location.', NULL, NULL, 1),
(303, 'Teachers Health Early Career Scholarship', 'The Public Education Foundation\'s Teachers Health Early Career Scholarship supports eligible public school teachers in the first three years of their career. The scholarship provides $12,000 to spend on approved professional development and learning, which may be used for a single course or a set of professional learning activities. Applications typically open in October each year.', 12000.00, 'FIXED', '2027-10-27', 140, 'https://www.nswtf.org.au/news/2025/10/16/2026-public-education-foundation-scholarships/', 'draft', '2026-05-03 10:55:09', '2026-05-14 12:41:45', 'Education', 'Merit-Based', 'Eligible public school teachers in the first three years of their career', NULL, NULL, 1),
(304, 'Australia for UNHCR Beddie Scholarship at AFTRS', 'The Public Education Foundation\'s Australia for UNHCR Beddie Scholarship at AFTRS supports individuals with a refugee background who intend to study film or television studies at a tertiary level at the Australian Film Television and Radio School (AFTRS). Applications typically open in October each year.', 12000.00, 'FIXED', '2027-10-28', 141, 'https://www.nswtf.org.au/news/2025/10/16/2026-public-education-foundation-scholarships/', 'active', '2026-05-03 10:55:09', '2026-05-14 12:48:50', 'Arts', 'Need-Based', 'For individuals with a refugee background who intend to study film or television studies at a tertiary level in 2026. Applicants who have not applied for the AFTRS Bachelor of Arts Screen: Production course by Wednesday, 8 October 2025 will not be considered for this scholarship.', NULL, NULL, 1),
(307, 'Westpac Future Leaders Scholarship', 'The Westpac Future Leaders Scholarship supports outstanding postgraduate coursework and research students eager to make a difference in Australia. Scholars receive funding for postgraduate studies and living expenses, access to leadership and mentorship programs, overseas travel opportunities, and networking experiences with industry leaders. Up to 17 scholarships are awarded annually to individuals commencing postgraduate study at one of nine partner universities in priority areas including Australia in Asia, technology, social change, and sustainability. Applications typically open June–July annually. Check website from June 2026.', 120000.00, 'FIXED', '2026-08-27', 144, 'https://scholars.westpac.com.au/scholarships/future-leaders-scholarship/', 'active', '2026-05-05 04:56:03', '2026-05-14 12:41:33', 'Technology | Other', 'Merit-Based', 'To be eligible for a 2026 Westpac Future Leaders Scholarship you must:\nBe an Australian citizen or permanent resident.\nHave completed your first undergraduate degree from 2020, or will complete your degree by 31 December 2025.\nHave achieved, or are on track to achieve, an average result of H1 or H2A equivalent or approx 75 WAM (the application form includes questions to provide further context to grades if required).\nHave chosen to undertake a full-time Masters by Coursework or Research or a PhD at one of our nine participating university partners.\nMust commence study in by July 2026. Current postgraduate students are not eligible.\nMD and Juris Doctor programs or a Masters by Coursework program longer than 2 years are also excluded.\nStudy in an area that will contribute to the future of Australia in one of the Trust\'s priority funding areas: Australia in Asia, Thriving Tech Sector, An Inclusive Australia and Sustainable Futures.\nInclude in your proposed program of study international opportunities which will develop your leadership skills and global networks, such as study tours for the purpose of research, attending a short course or conference, a period of internship or volunteering.\nHave a worthy and viable post-study plan that benefits Australia.\nSupply two letters of reference, one academic reference and one personal reference. Reference templates provided once applications launch.\nIf a finalist, be able to attend the interviews with the National Selection Panel in Sydney (Wednesday 3rd and Thursday 4th December). Westpac Scholars Trust will cover domestic travel costs for finalist to attend.\nBe able to attend the Future Leaders Scholars Leadership Development Program in Sydney in mid-February and another date, to be confirmed, in August/September 2026.\nBe able to attend the Westpac Scholars Summit on 29th & 30th April 2026.', NULL, NULL, 1),
(308, 'Harris Family Equity Scholarship', 'Supports undergraduate commencing students from low-socioeconomic status backgrounds and/or socio-educationally disadvantaged schools at UNSW. Provides $10,000 per annum for the minimum duration of the program.', 10000.00, 'FIXED', '2027-04-24', 120, 'https://www.scholarships.unsw.edu.au/scholarships/id/1961', 'active', '2026-05-13 13:11:23', '2026-05-14 12:41:33', NULL, 'Need-Based', 'Commencing Undergraduate, UAC & EAS, High School, Aus Citizen / Aus Permanent Resident / NZ Citizen', NULL, NULL, 1),
(309, 'UNSW Access Scholarship', 'Assists commencing undergraduate coursework students to undertake studies at UNSW Sydney. An equity-based scholarship supporting access to higher education.', 0.00, 'FIXED', '2027-04-24', 120, 'https://www.scholarships.unsw.edu.au/scholarships/id/1961', 'draft', '2026-05-13 13:11:23', '2026-05-14 11:34:56', NULL, 'Need-Based', 'Commencing Undergraduate, High School, Aus Citizen / Aus Permanent Resident / NZ Citizen, Assists commencing undergraduate coursework students to undertake studies at UNSW', 'Varies - contact UNSW equity team', NULL, 1),
(310, 'UNSW President & Vice-Chancellor\'s Equity Scholarship', 'Assists commencing undergraduate and postgraduate coursework students to undertake studies at UNSW Sydney. Provides $5,000 per annum for the minimum duration of the program.', 5000.00, 'FIXED', '2027-04-24', 120, 'https://www.scholarships.unsw.edu.au/scholarships/id/1961', 'active', '2026-05-13 13:11:23', '2026-05-14 12:41:33', NULL, 'Need-Based', 'Commencing Undergraduate and Postgraduate, UAC & EAS, Aus Citizen / Aus Permanent Resident / NZ Citizen', NULL, NULL, 1),
(311, 'Bertha McKenzie Postgraduate Indigenous Scholarship', 'Supports Indigenous students commencing a Masters by Coursework degree program at UNSW Sydney. Provides $22,500 per annum for the minimum duration of the program (up to 2 years).', 22500.00, 'FIXED', '2027-04-24', 120, 'https://www.scholarships.unsw.edu.au/scholarships/id/1961', 'active', '2026-05-13 13:11:23', '2026-05-14 12:48:50', NULL, 'Need-Based', 'Postgraduate commencing students, Indigenous Australian, Aus Citizen / Aus Permanent Resident / NZ Citizen, undertaking a Masters by Coursework degree program', NULL, NULL, 1),
(312, 'UNSW Equity Award', 'Assists currently enrolled undergraduate or postgraduate coursework students with their studies at UNSW Sydney. Provides $5,000 for one year.', 5000.00, 'FIXED', '2027-04-24', 120, 'https://www.scholarships.unsw.edu.au/scholarships/id/1961', 'active', '2026-05-13 13:11:23', '2026-05-14 12:48:50', NULL, 'Need-Based', 'Currently enrolled undergraduate or postgraduate coursework students, Aus Citizen / Aus Permanent Resident / NZ Citizen', NULL, NULL, 1),
(313, 'UNSW Pre-Entry & Enabling Programs Grant', 'Assists students commencing an approved enabling or pre-entry program at UNSW, including UNSW Prep Program, University Preparation Program, UNSW Indigenous Admission Scheme, and UNSW Indigenous Preparatory Programs. Provides $5,000 for one year for full-time programs.', 5000.00, 'FIXED', '2027-04-24', 120, 'https://www.scholarships.unsw.edu.au/scholarships/id/1961', 'draft', '2026-05-13 13:11:23', '2026-05-14 12:45:19', NULL, 'Need-Based', 'Assists students who are commencing an approved enabling or pre-entry program at UNSW, including: UNSW Prep Program (17–19 years), University Preparation Program (Mature Age Pathway), UNSW Indigenous Admission Scheme, UNSW Indigenous Preparatory Programs', NULL, NULL, 1),
(314, 'Community Plus Scholarship', 'Supports commencing students from low socioeconomic backgrounds with on-campus accommodation at UNSW Sydney. Provides up to $25,000 per annum towards residential fees for the minimum duration of the program.', 25000.00, 'FIXED', '2027-04-24', 120, 'https://www.scholarships.unsw.edu.au/scholarships/id/1961', 'draft', '2026-05-13 13:11:23', '2026-05-14 12:42:25', NULL, 'Need-Based', 'Commencing students from low socioeconomic backgrounds, Must secure a place with UNSW owned and operated on-campus accommodation provider, Aus Citizen / Aus Permanent Resident / NZ Citizen', NULL, NULL, 1),
(315, 'UNSW Accommodation Scholarship', 'Assists commencing undergraduate or postgraduate coursework students with accommodation costs while studying at UNSW Sydney. Provides $25,000 per annum towards residential fees for the minimum duration of the program.', 25000.00, 'FIXED', '2027-04-24', 120, 'https://www.scholarships.unsw.edu.au/scholarships/id/1961', 'active', '2026-05-13 13:11:23', '2026-05-14 12:41:33', NULL, 'Need-Based', 'Commencing Undergraduate or Postgraduate, High School, Aus Citizen / Aus Permanent Resident / NZ Citizen, on-campus accommodation required', NULL, NULL, 1),
(316, 'Basser Endowed Indigenous Award', 'Supports commencing or current full-time undergraduate Indigenous students experiencing educational disadvantage and residing at Basser College at UNSW Sydney. Provides $5,000 for one year.', 5000.00, 'FIXED', '2027-04-24', 120, 'https://www.scholarships.unsw.edu.au/scholarships/id/1961', 'active', '2026-05-13 13:11:23', '2026-05-14 12:48:50', NULL, 'Need-Based', 'Supports commencing or current full-time undergraduate Indigenous students experiencing educational disadvantage and are residing at Basser College.', NULL, NULL, 1),
(317, 'Basser Equity Award', 'Supports commencing or current full-time undergraduate students experiencing educational disadvantage and residing at Basser College at UNSW Sydney. Provides support for one year.', 0.00, 'FIXED', '2027-04-24', 120, 'https://www.scholarships.unsw.edu.au/scholarships/id/1961', 'draft', '2026-05-13 13:11:23', '2026-05-14 11:34:56', NULL, 'Need-Based', 'Commencing or current full-time Undergraduate students experiencing educational disadvantage, residing at Basser College, Australian Citizen / Australian Permanent Resident / NZ Citizen', 'Varies based on need', NULL, 1),
(318, 'Engineering Indigenous Equity Scholarship', 'Assists and encourages Indigenous students experiencing educational disadvantage to undertake full-time undergraduate study in the Faculty of Engineering at UNSW Sydney. Provides $15,000 per annum for the minimum duration of the program (up to 5 years).', 15000.00, 'FIXED', '2027-04-24', 120, 'https://www.scholarships.unsw.edu.au/scholarships/id/1961', 'active', '2026-05-13 13:11:23', '2026-05-14 12:41:33', 'Engineering', 'Need-Based', 'Indigenous students, full-time undergraduate study in Faculty of Engineering, experiencing educational disadvantage, Aus Citizen / Aus Permanent Resident / NZ Citizen', NULL, NULL, 1),
(319, 'Tyree Women in Engineering Scholarship', 'Supports women from a disadvantaged background commencing undergraduate studies at the UNSW Faculty of Engineering who have attended a Gateway Partner School in Greater Western Sydney. Provides $25,000 per annum towards residential fees or as a stipend for the minimum duration of the program (up to 5 years).', 25000.00, 'FIXED', '2027-04-24', 120, 'https://www.scholarships.unsw.edu.au/scholarships/id/1961', 'active', '2026-05-13 13:11:23', '2026-05-14 12:41:33', 'Engineering', 'Need-Based', 'Women from a disadvantaged background, commencing undergraduate studies in Faculty of Engineering, attended a Gateway Partner School in Greater Western Sydney, Aus Citizen / Aus Permanent Resident / NZ Citizen', NULL, NULL, 1),
(320, 'Al Willis Scholarship in Mechanical and Manufacturing Engineering', 'Supports students with academic ability experiencing socio/economic circumstances in undertaking an undergraduate program offered by the School of Mechanical and Manufacturing Engineering at UNSW Sydney. Provides $10,000 per annum for the minimum duration of the program (up to 4 years).', 10000.00, 'FIXED', '2027-04-24', 120, 'https://www.scholarships.unsw.edu.au/scholarships/id/1961', 'active', '2026-05-13 13:11:23', '2026-05-14 12:48:50', 'Engineering', 'Merit-And-Need', 'Supports students with academic ability experiencing socio/economic circumstances in undertaking an undergraduate program offered by the School of Mechanical and Manufacturing Engineering.', NULL, NULL, 1),
(321, 'Moses Honours Year Equity Scholarship', 'Supports students commencing full-time studies in an Honours Year program in the School of Mathematics & Statistics at UNSW Sydney. Preference is given to students doing a double degree and/or a pure mathematics stream. Provides $10,000 for one year.', 10000.00, 'FIXED', '2027-04-24', 120, 'https://www.scholarships.unsw.edu.au/scholarships/id/1961', 'active', '2026-05-13 13:11:23', '2026-05-14 12:41:33', 'Science', 'Need-Based', 'Commencing full-time studies in Honours Year program in School of Mathematics & Statistics, Aus Citizen / Aus Permanent Resident / NZ Citizen', NULL, NULL, 1),
(322, 'John Ragnar Anderson Endowed Memorial Scholarship in Chemistry', 'Supports students undertaking an undergraduate degree program with a major in Chemistry at the UNSW School of Chemistry. Provides $5,000 for the remaining duration of the program.', 5000.00, 'FIXED', '2027-04-24', 120, 'https://www.scholarships.unsw.edu.au/scholarships/id/1961', 'active', '2026-05-13 13:11:23', '2026-05-14 12:48:50', 'Science', 'Merit-Based', 'Undergraduate students with a major in Chemistry at UNSW School of Chemistry, Aus Citizen / Aus Permanent Resident / NZ Citizen', NULL, NULL, 1),
(323, 'Theresa Lindsay Hayward Indigenous Social Work Award', 'Supports a currently enrolled Indigenous Australian student undertaking their third or fourth year field placement as part of the UNSW Bachelor of Social Work program.', 5000.00, 'FIXED', '2026-12-31', 120, 'https://www.scholarships.unsw.edu.au/scholarships/id/1901', 'active', '2026-05-13 13:11:23', '2026-05-14 11:34:56', 'Arts', 'Need-Based', 'Currently enrolled Indigenous Australian student undertaking their third or fourth year field placement as part of the UNSW Bachelor of Social Work program.', NULL, NULL, 1),
(324, 'Kamal Bamadhaj Memorial Scholarship', 'Established to support students commencing full-time studies in an Honours Year program in the Faculty of Arts, Design & Architecture at UNSW in one of the following specialisations: history, politics or developmental studies.', 5000.00, 'FIXED', '2026-12-31', 120, 'https://www.scholarships.unsw.edu.au/scholarships/id/1901', 'active', '2026-05-13 13:11:23', '2026-05-14 11:34:56', 'Arts', 'Need-Based', 'Established to support students commencing full-time studies in an Honours Year program in the Faculty of Arts, Design & Architecture in one of the following specialisations: history, politics or developmental studies.', NULL, NULL, 1),
(325, 'Origin Foundations Grant King Indigenous Scholarships', 'Assists Indigenous students commencing an undergraduate degree program in the Faculty of Science or Faculty of Engineering at UNSW. The $25,000 will be paid as accommodation fees directly to the accommodation provider, with any difference paid as a stipend. Recipients also receive a UNSW President and Vice-Chancellors Equity Scholarship valued at $5,000 per annum stipend.', 25000.00, 'FIXED', '2026-12-31', 120, 'https://www.scholarships.unsw.edu.au/scholarships/id/1901', 'active', '2026-05-13 13:11:23', '2026-05-14 11:34:56', 'Engineering', 'Need-Based', 'Indigenous students commencing an undergraduate degree program in the Faculty of Science or Faculty of Engineering at UNSW. Students must have applied and received an offer to a UNSW on-campus accommodation provider to be eligible.', NULL, NULL, 1),
(326, 'Dorothy Hughes Memorial Scholarship', 'Encourages Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander students to continue study in the Faculty of Law & Justice at UNSW.', 6000.00, 'FIXED', '2026-12-31', 120, 'https://www.scholarships.unsw.edu.au/scholarships/id/1901', 'active', '2026-05-13 13:11:23', '2026-05-14 11:34:56', 'Law', 'Need-Based', 'Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander students to continue study in the Faculty of Law & Justice at UNSW.', NULL, NULL, 1),
(327, '2026 General Merit Undergraduate Scholarships for Commencing Students', 'The 2026 General Merit Undergraduate Scholarships application is open for recent High School Leavers commencing any undergraduate coursework degree program in Term 1, 2026, who seek to use their academic, leadership and community engagement experience to make a positive contribution to UNSW.', 5000.00, 'FIXED', '2026-09-01', 120, 'https://www.scholarships.unsw.edu.au/scholarships/id/1891', 'active', '2026-05-13 13:11:23', '2026-05-14 12:48:50', NULL, 'Merit-Based', 'To be eligible, applicants must meet all the following criteria:\nBe an Australian Citizen, Permanent Resident (including Humanitarian Visa Holders) or New Zealand Citizen\nHave applied for admission to a UNSW undergraduate degree program commencing Term 1, 2026 (via UAC or by any other UNSW admissions scheme)\nBe commencing full-time undergraduate study in an eligible degree program\nRefer to the table above for any additional criteria.', NULL, NULL, 1),
(328, 'UNSW Women in Engineering Scholarship Program for Students Commencing Term 1, 2026', 'The UNSW Women in Engineering Scholarships Program aims to encourage and assist female students commencing studies in the Faculty of Engineering at UNSW.', 5000.00, 'FIXED', '2026-09-01', 120, 'https://www.scholarships.unsw.edu.au/scholarships/id/1879', 'active', '2026-05-13 13:11:23', '2026-05-14 12:48:50', NULL, 'Merit-Based', 'To be eligible for these scholarships, applicants must meet the following criteria in addition to the program requirements listed above:\nBe an Australian Citizen, Permanent Resident (including Humanitarian Visa Holders) or New Zealand Citizen; and\nBe a woman, non-binary or gender-diverse student', NULL, NULL, 1),
(329, 'UNSW Arts, Design & Architecture Undergraduate Scholarships for Students Commencing Term 1, 2026', 'The UNSW Arts, Design & Architecture Undergraduate Scholarships were established to enhance the opportunities of students to enrol in an undergraduate program of study within the UNSW Faculty of Arts, Design & Architecture.', 5000.00, 'FIXED', '2026-09-01', 120, 'https://www.scholarships.unsw.edu.au/scholarships/id/1882', 'active', '2026-05-13 13:11:23', '2026-05-14 12:48:50', NULL, 'Merit-Based', 'Be commencing undergraduate study in one of the following disciplines: Bachelor of Education (Primary), Bachelor of Education (Secondary), Bachelor of Education (Primary) (Honours)', NULL, NULL, 1),
(330, 'UNSW School Of Mathematics & Statistics Undergraduate Scholarships for students commencing Term 1, 2026', 'Mathematics & Statistics Merit Scholarships aim to encourage and assist students commencing studies in the School of Mathematics & Statistics at UNSW.', 5000.00, 'FIXED', '2026-09-01', 120, 'https://www.scholarships.unsw.edu.au/scholarships/id/1886', 'draft', '2026-05-13 13:11:23', '2026-05-14 12:43:07', NULL, 'Merit-Based', 'Be a rural applicant*\n\n*Must have lived in a rural, regional or remote area within the two years prior to the start of your UNSW studies. Check the Australian Standard Geographic Classification Remoteness Areas (ASGC-RA) system map to check your eligibility. All categories other than RA1 Major Cities of Australia are considered to be regional or remote with the exception of Hobart.', NULL, NULL, 1),
(331, 'Mike Cannon-Brookes Endowed Scholarship', 'The purpose of the Scholarship is to support students undertaking the Bachelor of Science/Bachelor of Science (Computer Science) program at UNSW.', 10000.00, 'FIXED', '2026-09-01', 120, 'https://www.scholarships.unsw.edu.au/scholarships/id/1490', 'active', '2026-05-13 13:11:23', '2026-05-14 12:48:50', NULL, 'Merit-Based', 'To be eligible, applicants must:\nBe Domestic students ((Australian Citizen, Permanent Resident (including Humanitarian Visa Holders) or New Zealand Citizen))\nBe commencing in the Bachelor of Science/Bachelor of Science (Computer Science) in Term 1, 2026.\n*If a suitable candidate can\'t be found from this program, then candidates from other dual Computer Science programs combined with a Science Faculty program can potentially be considered.', NULL, NULL, 1);
INSERT INTO `scholarships` (`id`, `title`, `description`, `amount`, `amount_type`, `deadline`, `organization_id`, `application_url`, `status`, `created_at`, `updated_at`, `industry`, `scholarship_type`, `eligibility_raw_text`, `benefits_text`, `conditions_text`, `requires_application`) VALUES
(332, 'UNSW Scholarships for Asylum Seekers and Refugee Students Commencing Term 1, 2026', 'UNSW offers a number of scholarships to support Asylum Seekers and Refugee students undertaking full-time coursework study at UNSW. Some scholarships will full or partial tuition fee payment, while others provide a stipend to assist with the costs associated with your studies.', 25000.00, 'FIXED', '2026-10-30', 120, 'https://www.scholarships.unsw.edu.au/scholarships/id/1897', 'draft', '2026-05-13 13:11:23', '2026-05-13 13:11:23', NULL, 'Merit-Based', NULL, NULL, NULL, 1),
(333, 'Peter Ware Equity Scholarship', 'Supports financially disadvantaged students commencing undergraduate or postgraduate coursework studies at UNSW. Provides $15,000 per annum for the minimum duration of the program.', 15000.00, 'FIXED', '2026-12-09', 120, 'https://www.scholarships.unsw.edu.au/scholarships/id/1878', 'draft', '2026-05-13 13:13:05', '2026-05-14 11:34:56', NULL, 'Need-Based', 'Supports financially disadvantaged students commencing undergraduate or postgraduate coursework studies at UNSW.', NULL, NULL, 1),
(334, 'John & Kay Burman and Family Equity Scholarship', 'Supports commencing undergraduate students from low-socioeconomic status backgrounds and/or socio-educationally disadvantaged schools at UNSW.', 25000.00, 'FIXED', '2026-12-09', 120, 'https://www.scholarships.unsw.edu.au/scholarships/id/1878', 'active', '2026-05-13 13:13:05', '2026-05-14 12:41:33', NULL, 'Need-Based', 'Commencing Undergraduate, UAC & EAS, Education Level: High School, Residency: Aus Citizen / Aus Permanent Resident / NZ Citizen. Year 12 student from an identified low-SES background. UAC will automatically generate an application for the Educational Access Scheme (EAS) as part of your UAC undergraduate application if the residential address (not PO Box) you entered in your UAC undergraduate application is identified by the Australian Bureau of Statistics as being in the lowest 25% of socio-economic disadvantage in Australia. Entering UNSW via the Gateway Admissions Pathway. You will automatically be considered for Equity Scholarships based on your UNSW Gateway Admissions Pathway application.', NULL, NULL, 1),
(335, 'Sir Arthur & Lady Renee George Endowed Scholarship', 'Supports students who completed their senior secondary education at St Spyridon College, Maroubra NSW to commence any undergraduate program at UNSW (except Arts and Social Sciences and Art and Design).', 15000.00, 'FIXED', '2026-12-09', 120, 'https://www.scholarships.unsw.edu.au/scholarships/id/1878', 'active', '2026-05-13 13:13:05', '2026-05-14 12:41:33', NULL, 'Need-Based', 'Commencing Undergraduate\nUAC & EAS\nEducation Level: High School\nResidency: Aus Citizen / Aus Permanent Resident / NZ Citizen\n\nYear 12 student from an identified low-SES background\nUAC will automatically generate an application for the Educational Access Scheme (EAS) as part of your UAC undergraduate application if the residential address (not PO Box) you entered in your UAC undergraduate application is identified by the Australian Bureau of Statistics as being in the lowest 25% of socio-economic disadvantage in Australia.', NULL, NULL, 1),
(336, 'Monica and Gary Robinson Equity Scholarship', 'Supports students from low socio-economic backgrounds studying at UNSW. Provides $8,000 per annum for the minimum duration of the program.', 8000.00, 'FIXED', '2026-12-09', 120, 'https://www.scholarships.unsw.edu.au/scholarships/id/1878', 'active', '2026-05-13 13:13:05', '2026-05-14 12:48:50', NULL, 'Need-Based', 'Commencing Undergraduate\nUAC & EAS\nEducation Level: High School\nMinimum Value: $5,000 available for Duration of program (minimum)\nResidency: Aus Citizen / Aus Permanent Resident / NZ Citizen\n\nYear 12 student from an identified low-SES background. UAC will automatically generate an application for the Educational Access Scheme (EAS) as part of your UAC undergraduate application if the residential address (not PO Box) you entered in your UAC undergraduate application is identified by the Australian Bureau of Statistics as being in the lowest 25% of socio-economic disadvantage in Australia.\n\nEntering UNSW via the Gateway Admissions Pathway. You will automatically be considered for Equity Scholarships based on your UNSW Gateway Admissions Pathway application.', NULL, NULL, 1),
(337, 'UNSW Veterans Scholarship', 'Supports former and transitioning Australian Defence Force Personnel or their dependents, who are experiencing disadvantage to study in any UNSW undergraduate or postgraduate coursework degree. Provides $5,000 per annum for undergraduate or $20,000 total for postgraduate programs. Applicants must submit evidence of Australian military service record directly to UNSW Scholarships.', 20000.00, 'FIXED', '2026-12-09', 120, 'https://www.scholarships.unsw.edu.au/scholarships/id/1878', 'active', '2026-05-13 13:13:05', '2026-05-14 12:48:50', NULL, 'Need-Based', 'Commencing Undergraduate, UAC & EAS, High School education level, Aus Citizen / Aus Permanent Resident / NZ Citizen residency requirement. Year 12 student from an identified low-SES background. Educational Access Scheme (EAS) is open to year 12 students who have encountered significant educational challenges during year 11 and/or 12.', NULL, NULL, 1);
INSERT INTO `scholarship_sources` (`id`, `scholarship_id`, `url`, `content_type`, `fetched_at`, `content_hash`, `raw_text`, `raw_bytes_path`) VALUES
(1, 147, 'https://www.westernsydney.edu.au/international/applying/fees-and-costs/scholarships', 'html', '2026-01-21 00:48:23', '069ac487b4153d0322ecc847e53f6324b4abf6d5e2618c695b12322319a0fe71', 'International Scholarships | Western Sydney University\nQuick Links\nQuick Links\nMake an enquiry\nEntry requirements\nFees and Costs\nInternational Student Course Guide\nFind an education agent\nImportant dates\nOrientation\nEnglish and academic pathway programs\nScholarships\nFrequently Asked Questions (FAQs)\nInformation for agents\nEducation Services for Overseas Students (ESOS)\nInternational Partnerships\nInformation in your language\nAgent Portal\n<div class=\"algolia-analytics\" data-promoted=\"${hit?._rankingInfo?.promoted}\" data-insights-query-id=\"${hit.__queryID}\" data-insights-object-id=\"${hit.objectID}\" data-insights-position=\"${hit.__position}\" data-cug=\"${hit?.meta?.cug}\"><a href=\"${hit.url}\">${hit.title}</a></div>\nNo Results Found.\n<div class=\"algolia-analytics\" data-promoted=\"${hit?._rankingInfo?.promoted}\" data-insights-query-id=\"${hit.__queryID}\" data-insights-object-id=\"${hit.objectID}\" data-insights-position=\"${hit.__position}\" data-cug=\"${hit?.meta?.cug}\"><a href=\"${hit.url}\">${hit.title}</a></div>\nNo Results Found.\n<div class=\"algolia-analytics\" data-promoted=\"${hit?._rankingInfo?.promoted}\" data-insights-query-id=\"${hit.__queryID}\" data-insights-object-id=\"${hit.objectID}\" data-insights-position=\"${hit.__position}\" data-cug=\"${hit?.meta?.cug}\"><a href=\"${hit.url}\">${hit.title}</a></div>\nNo Results Found.\n<div class=\"algolia-analytics\" data-promoted=\"${hit?._rankingInfo?.promoted}\" data-insights-query-id=\"${hit.__queryID}\" data-insights-object-id=\"${hit.objectID}\" data-insights-position=\"${hit.__position}\" data-cug=\"${hit?.meta?.cug}\"><a href=\"${hit.url}\">${hit.title}</a></div>\nNo Results Found.\n${html `<div class=\"global-search-panel\">\r\n        <div class=\"global-search__suggestions\">\r\n            ${recentSearches}\r\n            ${querySuggestions}\r\n        </div>\r\n		<div class=\"search-tab-container\">\r\n        <div class=\"search-tab\">\r\n            ${sources[0]}\r\n        </div>\r\n		<div class=\"search-tab \">\r\n            ${sources[1]}\r\n        </div>\r\n		<div class=\"search-tab \">\r\n            ${sources[2]}\r\n        </div>\r\n		<div class=\"search-tab \">\r\n            ${sources[3]}\r\n        </div>\r\n		</div>\r\n    </div>`}\nREGISTER INTEREST\nInternational Students\n<div class=\"algolia-analytics\" data-promoted=\"${hit?._rankingInfo?.promoted}\" data-insights-query-id=\"${hit.__queryID}\" data-insights-object-id=\"${hit.objectID}\" data-insights-position=\"${hit.__position}\" data-cug=\"${hit?.meta?.cug}\"><a href=\"${hit.url}\">${hit.title}</a></div>\nNo Results Found.\n<div class=\"algolia-analytics\" data-promoted=\"${hit?._rankingInfo?.promoted}\" data-insights-query-id=\"${hit.__queryID}\" data-insights-object-id=\"${hit.objectID}\" data-insights-position=\"${hit.__position}\" data-cug=\"${hit?.meta?.cug}\"><a href=\"${hit.url}\">${hit.title}</a></div>\nNo Results Found.\n<div class=\"algolia-analytics\" data-promoted=\"${hit?._rankingInfo?.promoted}\" data-insights-query-id=\"${hit.__queryID}\" data-insights-object-id=\"${hit.objectID}\" data-insights-position=\"${hit.__position}\" data-cug=\"${hit?.meta?.cug}\"><a href=\"${hit.url}\">${hit.title}</a></div>\nNo Results Found.\n<div class=\"algolia-analytics\" data-promoted=\"${hit?._rankingInfo?.promoted}\" data-insights-query-id=\"${hit.__queryID}\" data-insights-object-id=\"${hit.objectID}\" data-insights-position=\"${hit.__position}\" data-cug=\"${hit?.meta?.cug}\"><a href=\"${hit.url}\">${hit.title}</a></div>\nNo Results Found.\n${html `<div class=\"global-search-panel\">\r\n        <div class=\"global-search__suggestions\">\r\n            ${recentSearches}\r\n            ${querySuggestions}\r\n        </div>\r\n		<div class=\"search-tab-container\">\r\n        <div class=\"search-tab\">\r\n            ${sources[0]}\r\n        </div>\r\n		<div class=\"search-tab \">\r\n            ${sources[1]}\r\n        </div>\r\n		<div class=\"search-tab \">\r\n            ${sources[2]}\r\n        </div>\r\n		<div class=\"search-tab \">\r\n            ${sources[3]}\r\n        </div>\r\n		</div>\r\n    </div>`}\nWhere are you from?\nThis will help us find the right content for you.\nAre you an International student?\nLooks like you are viewing this page from Australia\nChange Country\nView Domestic\nInternational Students\nInternational Enquiries\n+61 2 9852 5499\nDiscover\nDiscover\nWestern Sydney University is ranked in the top 250 universities globally. Join students from over 170 countries who have turned passions into rewarding careers.\nWhy Western\nSuccess Stories\nRankings and Statistics\nMeet Our Students\nEvents\nOur Campuses\nBankstown City\nCampbelltown\nHawkesbury\nLiverpool City\nMelbourne\nParramatta City\nParramatta South\nPenrith\nIndonesia\nSydney City\nSydney Olympic Park\nWestmead\nAgents\nFind an Agent\nAbout Western\nProspective agent\nBrand, logo & mission\nAdmission procedures\nAgent information\nInternational Partnerships\nStudy abroad\nGo Global\nScholarships\nStudying\nStudying\nUnlock unlimited possibilities through studying with us. Learn more about Western Sydney University, our programs, applications and international study here.\nPrograms for your success\nWestern way of learning\nEntry Requirements\nPre-university pathways\nSetting up your studies\nEarly Offers\nApplying\nApplying\nNot sure where to begin to apply as an international student? Learn more about applications, finding an agent and other information to apply to study with us.\nFees and costs\nCost of tuition\nScholarships\nUS Financial Aid Program\nInternational Sibling Discount\n10% Alumni Postgraduate Discount\nHow to apply\nFind an Agent\nInternational Application System\nStudy abroad\nAfter you apply\nAbout your offer\nAccepting your offer\nPaying International Student Fees\nStudent visa\nEnrolment\nInternational Orientation\nFAQs\nScholarships\nScholarships FAQ\nArriving\nArriving\nGetting ready to study in Australia? Find out more about what to do to prepare before you leave, how to accept your offer, and what to do when you arrive.\nImportant dates\nPreparing to arrive\nWhat to bring\nBringing your family\nHealth cover\nEntering Australia and airport arrival\nBooking an airport pickup\nTips for the best uni life\nAccommodation\nExplore Accommodation Options\nUnder 18s\nAccommodation Scholarships\nCost of living\nInternational Orientation\nLife at Western\nLife at Western\nWestern has a range of initiatives that gives international students the best chance of success. Get a better idea of what we offer, and what Australia is like.\nHow Western supports you\nStudent support services\nStudent Central\nStudent Wellbeing\nDisability Service\nSports\nFood on campus\nLife in Australia\nClimate\nCulture\nSafety in Sydney\nSetting up your life\nShopping and food\nUtilities\nTransport\nManaging your money\nWorking in Australia\nCareers and Advice for International Students\nLife Beyond\nLife Beyond\nWestern\'s contribution to your success does not end at graduation. We have what it takes to support your continuous learning and professional development.\nScholarships\nWe offer one of Australia\'s most generous scholarship programs supporting international students, particularly those from developing countries, to pursue overseas study. All applicants for our coursework programs are automatically considered. Successful scholarship recipients will receive notification of their awards in their Offer of Admission letter.\nScholarships valued up to 50% of tuition fees.\nWhen you apply for a coursework program with Western Sydney University you will automatically be considered for an international scholarship. A separate application is not necessary.\nUndergraduate\nPostgraduate\nSustainable Development Goals\nPackaged Offers\nResearch\nExternal Scholarships\nAccommodation Scholarships\nScholarship Frequently Asked Questions\n1 on 1 Scholarship Advising Session\nUndergraduate\nWestern Sydney University has a range of scholarships available for international students seeking admission to undergraduate programs.\nScholarships valued at $6,000, $3,000 or 50% of tuition fees are awarded on academic merit.\nRegional Achievement Award\nInternational applicants from North Asia and South East Asia are eligible for either a AUD $5,000 or AUD $10,000 Regional Achievement Award, available for all 2026 intakes.\nTerms & Conditions\napply.\nMore about this scholarship\nInternational UAC Scholarship\nA $10,000 multi-year scholarship is awarded on the basis of academic merit as recognised by Western Sydney University for admission.\nTerms & Conditions\napply.\nMore about this scholarship\nVice-Chancellor\'s Academic Excellence Undergraduate Scholarships\nThis Scholarship recognises outstanding academic achievements and will cover 50% of the cost of tuition fees for three years. Applications are not necessary and successful students will be notified in the Offer of Admission letter.\nMore about this scholarship\nWestern Sydney International Scholarships - Undergraduate\nThis scholarship was introduced to provide our Undergraduate international students a smooth start to university. We offer a $6000 multi-year or $3000 multi-year partial scholarship to be applied towards tuition fees up to a maximum of three years.\nMore about this scholarship\nPostgraduate\nWestern Sydney University has a range of scholarships available for international students seeking admission to postgraduate programs.\nScholarships valued at $6,000, $3,000 or 50% of tuition fees are awarded on academic merit.\nRegional Achievement Award\nInternational applicants from North Asia and South East Asia are eligible for either a AUD $5,000 or AUD $10,000 Regional Achievement Award, available for all 2026 intakes.\nTerms & Conditions\napply.\nMore about this scholarship\nInternational UAC Scholarship\nA $10,000 multi-year scholarship is awarded on the basis of academic merit as recognised by Western Sydney University for admission.\nTerms & Conditions\napply.\nMore about this scholarship\nVice-Chancellor\'s Academic Excellence Postgraduate Scholarships\nTo encourage exceptional academic achievements of international Postgraduate applicants, this Scholarship will cover 50% of the cost of the tuition fees. Applications are not necessary and successful students will be notified in the Offer of Admission letter.\nMore about this scholarship\nWestern Sydney International Scholarships - Postgraduate\nThis Scholarship for Postgraduate international applicants recognises academic merit and offers a $6000 multi-year or $3000 multi-year partial scholarship to be applied towards tuition fees up to a maximum of two years.\nMore about this scholarship\nAlumni - International Scholarships\nThe International Alumni Scholarship offers $10,000 per year towards tuition fees, for up to three years (undergraduate) or two years (postgraduate).  All new international students commencing a CRICOS-registered degree in 2026 will be automatically considered based on academic merit — no separate application is required.\nThe scholarship is available across most undergraduate and postgraduate programs, with some exclusions, and is awarded on a first-come-first-served basis until filled.\nTerms & conditions\napply\nWestern Sydney University International Alumni Scholarship\nMore about this scholarship\nSustainable Development Goals - International Scholarships\nThese scholarships have been introduced to support Western Sydney University’s commitment to the United Nations Sustainable Development Goals.\nWestern Sydney University has been named number one in the world for its social, ecological and economic impact in the latest Times Higher Education (THE) University Impact Ranking, 2025.\nSustainable Development Goals - International Undergraduate Scholarship\nMore about this scholarship\nSustainable Development Goals - International Postgraduate Scholarship\nMore about this scholarship\nWestern Sydney University Vietnam\nAUS Access Scholarship\nWestern Sydney University is offering the AUS Access Scholarship to eligible undergraduate and postgraduate students at our Western Sydney University Vietnam.\nMore about this scholarship\nPackaged Offers\nWestern Sydney International EAP Scholarship\nThis Scholarship is for students with an eligible EAP packaged offer and provides a 20% discount on EAP fees for those commencing in 2026.\nMore about this scholarship\nResearch\nJoint Scholarships\nChina Scholarship Council (CSC) Research Scholarship\nGraduate Research School Scholarships\nMain Round Scholarships\nProject Scholarships\nExternal Scholarships\nAustralia Awards Scholarship\nThe Australia Awards Scholarship is a prestigious international scholarship funded by the Australian Government that aims to contribute to the long term development needs of Australia\'s partner countries, in line with bilateral and regional agreements. The scholarship provides students the opportunity to study in Australia to build the skills and knowledge to promote development in their home country/region. Scholarships are mainly at postgraduate level however there is a limited number of undergraduate scholarships (country/region specific).\nEligibility\nFor country/region-specific eligibility criteria, please see the\nAustralia Awards webpage\n.\nScholarship Value\nFull tuition fees, return home travel, establishment allowance, contribution to Living Expenses (CLE), Overseas Student Health Cover (OSHC), Supplementary Academic Support, air tickets for field trip (for research student only).\nApplication Process\nYou need to apply directly to the Australia Award managing office in your country/region to be considered for an Australia Award Scholarship. Closing dates vary from country/region to country/region. In most countries, applications fro scholarships close in approximately May of the previous year. For more information, view the\nAusaid participating countries page\n.\nAccommodation Scholarship\nAccommodation Scholarships are available for International students commencing their studies at Western Sydney University. Visit our Accommodation Scholarship webpage for more information.\nAccommodation Scholarships\nScholarship Frequently Asked Questions\nScholarship FAQs\nFrequently Asked Questions\n1 on 1 Scholarship Advising Session\nOnly students who wish to discuss something not found within their scholarship terms and conditions will be eligible for a 1 on 1 scholarship advising session.\nRequest scholarship advising session\nStudying at Western\nApplying to Western\nMake an enquiry\nArriving at Western\nFooter links\nAccessibility\nWebsite Feedback\nAdmissions Transparency\nComplaints Unit\nDisclaimer\nPrivacy\nRight to Information\nInformation in your language\nContact Us\n+61 2 9852 5499\nEmail Us\nWestern Sydney University\nLocked Bag 1797\nPenrith NSW 2751\nFollow Us\nWestern Sydney University Copyright ©\n2004-2026\nABN 53 014 069 881\nCRICOS Provider No: 00917K\nTEQSA Provider ID: PRV12061 (Australian University)\nTop 50 Universities under 50 years old\nEmployer of Choice For Women', NULL),
